reviews.text: Listen .. the fish was absolutely amazing! It was seasoned so well that you didn't need any kind of sauce for it. Speaking of sauce (the little dish in the picture) .. it was SOOO spicy the way I like it. (I'm from Louisiana just so you know my spice level). Oh, they only take cash so come ready with Euros. There are certain dishes you'd have to call a day in advance for them to prepare. So when you call to make a reservation ask if they can have whatever dish you want. I recommend this place!

The Eru soup was super! The grilled fish my friend had was so big she couldn't finish it. The price was good too, though the grilled fish seem to have a variable price. I'll be there again when next I'm in Stuttgart or maybe just even drive to Stuttgart just to enjoy a meal there!

The food was excellent and true to taste of West African Cuisine.  Although they do not accept creat at this time they were very service oriented and accommodating. Plus having access to watch a football match while you eat was fantastic. It terms of space it is comparable to a German restaurant.

Very cool place i entered for the first time. Black people are so handsome here, make sure you also be handsome :) i tried Okra for the first time. It is good that you put your menu in your google info.
One of the best restaurants ever the service is wonderful the food and to grown it all the hygiene is awesome can't pass a week without having the test of thier meal

editorial_summary.overview: Flatbreads, couscous & pan-continental game dishes at a cozy stop with classic African motifs.

reviews.text: Absolutely great. Called them a few minutes before closing time and ask if we could still come by and we could. Unfortunately, most of the kitchen was already cleaned up and we could not order some of the premium dishes - but understandable. The service was great: polite and quick (past their opening times). The food was exceptional, tasty and the price was on point. Will make sure to come back to try the crocodile meat and desserts that we not managed to order past closing time :D
One of the better places we've visited in Stuttgart. The food was cooked very well and was seasoned to perfection. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking to get a good meal.

Great kitchen, i loved the food.
Bad Restaurant, uncomfortable floor seating, bad ventilation, weak lights make it hard to read menus, they make you sit on the floor with strangers at the same table because it's overcrowded.
Staff is bad at their job: slow, forgetful of orders, mixes everything up, food arrives late, cold and often wrong.
If you can't eat spicy or specifically want your food spicy make sure to remind them 3 or 4 times.
Would not recommend going there untill they improve their service staff and seating area. Again the food was delightful

The food was pretty good! Pricey, but good quantity of food. I had a vegetarian dish and the husband had a meat platter. Staff was very friendly and speak English well. Best to make a reservation because it gets quite busy for dinner. Street parking available and within walking distance of u-bahn/bus stop.

Very lovely place. Atmosphere 100%. I’m a bit old to stay on the small pillows on the ground very funny situation overall. Spicy mojito one of the best things in the world. The food is nice. Always a pleasure to visit.

editorial_summary.overview: Spicy meat stews, flatbreads & traditional East African food in a colorful dining room.

reviews.text: Wonderful food and atmosphere. Very friendly personal. When it's full, one has to wait a little since they're low on staff...but taste of the food makes the wait worth it 😊

Ebony gave me my first ever taste of African/Eriterian food thanks to my colleague’s recommendation. First of all, I really loved the ambience which was little bit hipster and little bit cozy with a lot of artistic touches. Now coming to the food, I was really taken away by the homely taste of the food. The starter was great and the main dish was even better (also too much quantity). They even had samosa (we have the same in India too). Also, Injera, the main part of the dish is very similar to the indian food dosa. It’s like we share a bond with Africa through food. We are all the same.

Our first time trying Eritrean dishes. Very friendly staffs and the food was absolutely delicious. Well recommended! Parking could be a little bit difficult in the evening but you could just park few blocks away from the restaurant. Or take a train there 😊
Thank you for the excellent service and keep up the good work!

Amazing spot! Great beer selection and a wide variety of dishes. I started with the vegetable soup and then tried the sampler for one to taste a little bit of everything. Chicken was fall-off-the-bone and the injera was fantastic. Highly recommend!
Amazing, I have been in three African restaurants in Stuttgart but this is definitely the best, price and food are TOP and the service is extremely kind.
A good indigenous experience combined with mouthwatering food makes it a place for a must visit.
Super cute place to have very good African food. We really liked it :)
Makamba is one the, if not the best restaurant I know. The food is delightful and the place is very comfortable. The staff is very nice and open for conversations. Definitely recommend this gem!!
I have been in several Ethiopian restaurants. Makamba has been the best of all. Vegetables and meat with lots of flavor make a great combo with just the right fluffy bread. Totally recommend it.

Very disappointing. We waited 30 min to get the menu, another 30 min until someone took our order and then almost an hour until our food came.
The food was ok but cold and overpriced for a very small portion.

editorial_summary.overview: Exotic meats like zebra & crocodile, plus vegetarian options, in a low-lit, tentlike dining room.

reviews.text: The place Madagascar has a very authentic atmosphere supported by a very soft but local music. You feel like being in Africa. The Menu contains a lot of special dishes. The meat dishes are containing an awesome variety offered for a higher price than average (25-30€). I ate a vegetarian dish which tasted really good and gave me a lot of different flavor to taste from. The price was reasonable (below 20€) and drinks are as usual. the cool stuff they have are place were you sit on the ground or knew on the ground. The floor is covered with sand so you feel not like being in Stuttgart 😎.

First of all, this restaurant is gorgeous 😍. The decoration is on point. The staff is really nice. The toilets were clean and beautiful to look at and to use. The paintings made me feel on vacation somewhere in Africa 🙌🏾. The food was delicious 😋. I tried sea food and different cocktails. The cassava chips were super crispy and reminded me of home. We had dessert too. And a lot of fun 😌.
Very good and polite service, beautiful and cozy place. Food is ok, cocktails- great.

I took a plate with chicken, vegetables and rice in a coconut sauce and it was so taste! Nice decoration with nice music from Africa. Very educated and sympathetic waitress. Unfortunately they were not accepting credit cards.

Loved it! Great atmosphere and nice staff. If you are not sure ask them, team is great in recommending meals. Unfortunately, we have to wait for a long time to get main course, it was crowded and I thing they were understaffed. But we will come again!

editorial_summary.overview: Vibrant, retro-themed diner with patio seating offering creative burgers, hot dogs & comfort fare.

reviews.text: One of the very few restaurants in Stuttgart with “air conditioning”. Nice and cool inside on a sunny day. Very good hamburger (big), awesome French Fries and a gigantic selection of beverages including 19 different beers (biers). Overall the best hamburger I’ve had in Stuttgart in two years.

This place is great! The restaurant itself was super adorable with classic American Diner decor and oldies playing. They have 3 vegan burger options! We have gone twice now and both times have been FANTASTIC! We've had both the Planty Classic Plus burger (Beyond Meat cheezeburger) and the Vegantastic One cheezeburger! They were both awesome! My favorite is definitely the Vegantastic One!!! :D Their lemonades are absolutely phenomenal too--our faves are the mint and the strawberry rhubarb!! The staff was great--super sweet and friendly. We definitely will go back again and again! We already have plans to go back again next week! :)

We had a reservation at a nearby Mexican restaurant named after a city in Texas, but because we wer 40 minutes early were told to wait outside in the cold. They were open and only one table was in use.
Google led me to Jakes and we were squeezed in between two reservations. Knowing our time was limited, we ate as quickly as possible.
The entire experience was pleasant. The service was friendly, and we felt good and appreciated for being there.
The food was amazing. I could go in about how great everything looked, and tasted, I was so hungry I didnt bother to check my pictures, so they aren't very good quality compared to what we got.  If you are nearby, go to Jakes. Because you will not be disappointed.

This place is Awesome! The wife and I stopped by today because we saw they had chicken wings. We got and order of the wings and chicken crossies which are like chicken nuggets but made of whole chicken not ground chicken. The food was delicious! Their curly fries taste amazing. The staff is super friendly and they speak English. We highly recommend this place to get your american style burger & chicken wings. We will definitely come back and try their burgers.

I love this place! They have the best burgers I've ever tasted, and I was all over Europe during the 3 years I lived there. I lived less than 200m away from Jake's and visited frequently. What's best is that they upgraded their menu and have 3 vegan burgers to choose from, that are unbelievably tasty, plus many other traditiknal tasty burgers. My only complaint about this place is that they're not open on Sundays. That's it! 😁

reviews.text: Best experience ever, the food was amazing, so many vegan options!!! The stuff was so helpful and cheerful and the decorations and overall aesthetic was beautiful!!!!

Excellent service: very beautiful ladies, very welcoming, always making jokes and comfortable atmosphere. Amazingly decorated place with a catchy menu that will make u want to try out everything. Love the milkshakes. Perfect place for an american burger lunch/dinner.

Amazing food , but its a bit more overpriced and expensive .
The staff are super nice and friendly , we waited outside for the table , so they got us a heater and some hot drinks until a table is ready , they are always smiling .
The burgers are great , very good flavour combinations , curly fries was very good .
But the prices are not , from a value for money perspective it is more than a little overpriced .
It is a really cool experience anyway and a must visit.
Great ambiance! Feels like you are somewhere in the US. I took the ladies burger. It was a great! I have to go back to try out the sandwiches and the shakes someday soon 😅

Different spot to go to and have a burger made for you.  The style of the environment is very nice with an old flare as well as the choice of items on the menu.  Employees are very nice and inviting.  Good place to go with a good atmosphere to switch it up with good food.

Small beer selection and lots of space. Beers were good AND they had Tusker!!! (Delicious!)
Would go again.

Good place to get together for events.  Drinks are good. Not too expensive. Only negative was that they only take US dollars. No euros and no cards. As long as you know that in advance, you're good!

Update: The Kelley Club has been remodeled and looks great! They also may take cards now... Woot woot!

A little History
During the Cold War Era this was a US Army Officer's Club. It also allowed Senior NCOs during my time there (1982-86).

As a photographer for VII Corps I spent more than a little time there during official events like the annual New Year's Party which hosted most of the Commanders of the various NATO forces in Central Europe. It was so big in the 1980's under (then LTG) John Galvin that they actually had two parties- the earlier one for the lower ranking Officers and Civilians and the later one for the big shots.
They even hired a German Chimney Sweep to hand out a new penny to each guest. These had to be flown in from the US, as overseas at that time the PX and Commissary rounded up transactions instead of bringing pennies over.
Great food, family friendly environment, very nice staff. Can be crowded during peak hours or events. Would recommend.
Had some of their catered food and it tasted really good. The staff was courteous.

editorial_summary.overview: Striking, spacious locale offering pan-Asian dishes & wine, plus a buffet option.

reviews.text: We felt we are having for Gala dinner. Ambience is very nice. Soothing to eyes and looks very amazing. Buffet was good. Mangolian grill was nice, had multiple meat options, however it was prepared little over salted. We liked the options of desert, ice creams as those were not mere formalities but really good quality and tastes better than other places. Saturday were very very long queues outside, luckily we had reservation but still had to wait 20mins to arrive to table. Reservation on Weekend is recommended. It was still with the wait. Price was moderate to high on weekend, else quite reasonable on weekdays. One of cool and nice place to have family dinner outside. A lot of native Chinese people were there tells you the authenticity of restaurant. Definitely worth visit.

The service is okay, the food is great, clean place, the sushi variety is okay ( could be better), good price for the value. About one or two hours before they close, the buffet is poor, specially the 🍣 sushi 🍣.  Otherwise every thing is okay .

Everything is amazing: food is delicious, it's huge variety of different foods, ambience is absolutely stunning and beautiful, looks very luxurious, the staff is very kind and friendly, you won't be missing or waiting for anything.

I love the open buffet (all you can eat) which they offer.
Food is fresh, different Sortiments of meet and delicious desserts for a fare price.
Perfect place, service and food. There is a big variety of Asian food and sweets. The only negative is they don't have their menu in the buffet in English.

Terrible! We ordered for delivery, didn’t manage to do much investigation ahead of time and that’s a regret. Sushi platter is all vegetarian- that alone should come with a warning label! Couldn’t tell one dish from the next, we literally ate one bite of everything o taste and threw the food Away. Total waste...
I had buffet here . And it's was worth for the price .. and I will visit once again...
Good food, good sushi, decent prices. Lately became a bit more expensive than it used to be.
Delicious food, good portions, good service, reasonable prices.
The Soups are the best. We drive 10 KMS just so that we can have hot hot soups. :)
Pretty good food, good portions, helpful service. Very pleased, worth to come back!

Very bad quality and taste.
Pad thai was extremelly bad, sushi as well.
Very nice family ❣️ atmosphere food is great

I told them to make spicy but it was not as spicy as I want.
Rest everytthng is fine, Overall good.
Can only visit once.
Authentic vietnamese food (I've not tried the other cuisine here). The Pho is great when not feeling too good. Very reasonable prices, great staff. Very friendly

reviews.text: Always very fast and very fresh food. Staff is very friendly and cute, mostly Vietnamese, really nice guys. Great for quick dinner!

My review not based on Food but based on service. Food is quite good. Also the ambience and location are perfect. However, the service lady was not very much friendly and left me unattended just for Order around 15mins, although it was not that crowded. On mentioning about the wait, instead of acknowledging, she said it was just 5 min (not 15min) as I complained. A similar wait was there for billing. I ended up being there 70mins where it could have been easily done in 30mins. Service very poorly managed.

The ginger tea was delicious! The food came in quicker than I expected ...and it was muah! Service was good.  Rather unfortunate that they only accept cash payment. Card payment would have been top! ;)

Taking away the finished plate, the waitress asked me: “Was it perfect?”. :)
A strange question might you think, but damn it was!

The place is very very simple, but the food is amazing. Served quickly and the portions are quite big. Give it a try.

I came here for dinner, the food was served rather fast. The kitchen was a bit smelly though.

Now to the food- it was average..

The seats are not movable nor are the tables   so your stuck to rat in the same spot.

the ambience was pretty good.

Overall, even though I won't come to eat here again I still think you should try it out... But beware of the extremely large proportions..;)

Very delicious authentic Vietnamese food!
We have tried the green curry with crispy fried chicken,  it was really good although not spicy at all. The chicken was very crispy and fresh.
The soups were very delicious as well. I have particularly loved the tapioca banana pudding. It is made with milk, tapioca pearls, peanuts and bananas I guess, it was unique and tasty.

Stopped by today for lunch, this place is well worth the trip. The wait staff is very good and took our order right away. The food is inexpensive and vell prepared. Authentic Vietnamese comfort food that you can crave for over again. Definitely will be coming back...
Delicious and authentic Vietnamese cuisine. Duck 🦆 is amazing. Fried rice and curry are both great. But I love the rice noodles with beef! No parking but try the lots nearby.
Very very good vietnamese and Southeast Asian dishes. ✨
Spring rolls and veggies were fresh. Beef cooked perfectly. Rice was fresh. Would recommend.
Great place for an asian meal with lots of varieties. The fried rice was delicious and made me wanna eat more. The pricing is also quite reasonable. Will go there again for sure!

Delicious milk tea! It is one of the places that actually offers low sugar milk tea. Normally, I find taro milk teas (even with 30%) too sweet, however, this place had one with almost no sugar at all :)

I bought the bubble tea and fried noodles yesterday and got acute gastroenteritis. I've got heavy stomachache and diarrhea and went to to emergency room. But none of the employees here can speak English so I even don't know how to let them know my illness. I would not recommend anyone to eat in this restaurant, never!!
Got V1 and it was great... They don't speak German... Or very little
They sent the wrong order after waiting for over an hour and a half, and then refused to refund us. Will never order from here again.

reviews.text: Delicious food for little money. We get some take out meals almost every week and have never been disappointed. Friendly and attentive staff and quick food preparation. The big portions are also a plus. Would definitely recommend 🙂

One of the Hidden gem in Esslingen center. Best Asian food and we really like their hospitality and of course their food.. they give feel that you are asian home.
The last treat you like you are their family guest.

I still remember when we were there, one blind person came, the lady was taking care of him and explaining every food and tasted. Impressed.

Nice ambience. A quiet and peaceful place. Plenty of place to sit.
Fresh and tasteful food. Can be customised according to your needs (mild, spicy, dragon mouth spicy ;-), different sauce, extra veggies) anything.
Prices are great, portions are big but most importantly everything arrives fresh, crispy and hot. Plenty of vegetarian options.
Definitely recommended.

Hmmm just tried the Winter Menü, really nice 👌
Scampi tempura with tamarind sauce as first plate.
Duck with maracuja (passion fruit) sauce (home made) for the main dish.
Yummy home made coco-vanilla desert.
Lovely dinner.

The food was average, even a bit less ...big portions though
Prices are not aligned with quality
Maybe they have something special in their menu, but not going to try again

Very friendly service at a comfortable restaurant and we were craving some Chinese food after a week of good German food. Pleasantly surprised by the tasty and very substantial serving of two soup noodles, pork ribs and mayo tofu with rice. For our Asian appetites I’d say order 3 mains and it will comfortably serve 4.

We had a good experience it is it Sichuan food 🤩 absolutely loved the beef dishes (we had both spicy and the sour one!) and the lotus salad 🥗 on top of all the ribs were absolutely delicious 🤤 we totally recommend it to people who would love to try out sichuan food ✨

My friend recommended me this Chinese restaurant for its authentic Chinese cuisine. We went for a spontaneous lunch there. We were greeted by friendly staff. We ordered fried Kung Pao chicken, garlic eggplant and fried pork intestine. The dishes were very tasty and authentic.

The staff was attentive but you did have to spend some effort to get their attention.

The restaurant itself is small and well decorated.

In conclusion, a restaurant where you can find tasty authentic Chinese cuisine. If you want to try really real Chinese food from southeast China than I highly recommend this restaurant.
I recommend this Chinese restaurant, is just on the train station. The food is really tasty 🌶️. The atmosphere could be improved with some ambient music.
Food is authentic Chinese. Love it. Service could speak more German 😅 love it and will come again 👍

editorial_summary.overview: Basic Chinese joint offering classic stir-fries, seafood & appetizers from a buffet or à la carte.

reviews.text:
Spoiler alert! Not a great experience at Mulan garden
-Too expensive food for very little variety (especially if you are a vegetarian).
-The place looks dull with old furniture and the owner/counter lady comes off a bit too arrogant, this just puts off the whole experience of dining in here.
-No Heaters were on when it was freezing cold.
-Very cold food from the buffet counter was served. Especially, some starters looked soggy and dried up, needed a quick and hot refill.
-Chinese beer was good as it is first-pressed.
-Outside ambience is better than inner ambience, therefore still worth a try in Summer.
-oh yeah! CASH only

Giving them 4 stars due to friendly service and a clean washroom- something that can often overlooked in Europe.

I do wish I had read the reviews before coming.

Unfortunately it was one of the few buffets where I didn't feel I quite got my money's worth. I've got a bottomless stomach, so if a buffet is tasty enough I can practically run them out of business. Lucky for Mulan garden this was not the case. I found the flavors to be a little bland, with not many options. As others have mentioned, the temperature can be a little worrying. My partner enjoyed the food more than me, and currently we both feel fine after eating.

I think for some people it can be a good option, but for me I had some regrets eating here.

I liked this place. It is more 4 stars, than 5 stars place, but I am giving 5 because of all the haters. When you take all you can eat, you get solid variety of dishes. It is clean, service is good. Don't listen to haters, it really is a descent place. I'll be back :)

Gave this a shot since it was one of the few places on the delivery app that had fried rice.

Food
I got the Beef fried rice and egg rolls. The egg roll was not what I want expected. Usually it's maybe 2 or three regular sized rolls but this one was just one massively big one. It was at least hot but ok flavor wise. Fried rice looked like it would have alot of flavor but not much and the beef seemed like it was added after the rice as a whole was fried.

Service
Delivery was within the 30 minutes and no issues with the packaging.

Overall
Definitely not interested in trying this place again and recommend to looking elsewhere.

Worst buffet in town, very limited starter and main course menu,  compared to other chinese buffet restaurant this one is not up to the mark. Only positive side is the location of the restaurant which is located in the mitte. Not recommended

editorial_summary.overview: Noodles, rice dishes & other Chinese standards presented in a laid-back mainstay.

reviews.text:
Great authentic Chinese restaurant with an extensive menu.
The steamed fish and seafood pot were very fresh and delicious. We also liked the homemade table condiment which was savoury and added a lot of flavor to our noodle dish.
The service was very friendly and accommodating.
The food could have been better. There was too much of turmeric on the Chicken Fried Rice. The noodle was too oily to the point that it was dripping oil. The other chicken curry with rice was okay.
Amazing Cantonese style food! Definitely recommend ordering from the Chinese language menu, they have pictures for foreigners, too!

We came here very late on a Monday night. Initially we could only order take-out, but since we didn’t have a place to take it away to (we were about to drive home that night), they made an exception. That was super sweet in itself but then the food turned out to be really good as well. Hearty, delicious Thai and Kantonese food. Glad we came here!

Arrived at a cold Wednesday night after a long business trip. The service can’t be more friendly compared to some so called « 5 star » local restaurants. THANKS FOR THE KINDNESS, THANKS FOR THE GREAT FOOD, WILL SURELY COME BACK!

reviews.text: Absolutely amazing food. Would highly recommend. Amazing value for money

Update (Jan 2023): The prices have increased dramatically...evening buffet for 28€ now...! Too expensive...

Original review (Aug 2022):
Used to be very good, quality have decreased slightly. Very recommended from Mo-Saturday during lunch including free drinks and coffee. Price is pretty affordable because it is including drinks. For dinner and Sundays it is not too recommended cause of the high price. They charge additionally for pretty expensive drinks!

Besides that, food is good and they have quite a variety! :)
Had a buffet lunch there. Not too bad. Things are fresh. Their soft drinks could have improved a bit more. Taste is slightly off. Love their salad

The price for the buffet is ok (28€) but you have to pay extra for every single drink you order. Food has good flavour and it didn't unbalance my stomach, so good hygiene. The staff is kind and helpful. Location and ambience also ok.

Best chinese buffet I have ever been so far. Big variety of food to choose from and every food I tasted was good. Very often I take on the plate different options, and there is always some huge disappointments that I just cannot eat, but this buffets every food I tasted, was so good that I finally almost managed to empty my plate. Also the soups are worth to try, I really loved the Tom Yam Gai soup, and did eat 3 bowls of it, because it was so good. Will visit again for sure! 6 points out of 5. Thanks!

editorial_summary.overview: Straightforward counter-serve outfit dishing up traditional Chinese specialties.

reviews.text: I would say this is a happy place for Chinese people. The food taste quite similar but I wouldn’t say it taste delicious. When you choose what dish you want, the server will put it on the plate for you. Each dish cost x amount and if you want to try a little bit of everything it might cost at least €10.

A very authentic Chinese restaurant! It is not with typical Chinese restaurant-style dishes in Europe (too oily, salty, fried or sweet), rather they offer Chinese home cooking dishes - simple, fresh, tasty and healthy.
Best place for Chinese people craving for Chinese food.

Best Chinese ca fine food in Stuttgart! Feeling hungry and need some healthy and delicious Asian food? Head here! Catine-style ready good to select from OR one of the awesome noodle soups! Best Chinese place in downtown Stuttgart!!!
Authentic Chinese food to crave it for in stuttgart, you never get disappointed with veg friendly options... Spiciness adjusted to your taste buds

editorial_summary.overview: Casual Chinese eatery offering classic meat & seafood dishes, plus noodles & rice.

reviews.text: Been here many times, though I had a solo lunch this afternoon. The service was friendly and the food was usually not too bad, with a decent variety if you looked at the Chinese menu. We never order from the limited German lunch menu which is cheaper, but uninteresting.
Very tasty and authentic. The place is huge and it was crowded even on weekday afternoon. Also kids friendly. Fast service.

This is a really typical and delicious Chinese restaurant with reasonable price. I like the spicy food here which really recall the feeling of my family. If you want to try special Chinese food, this will be a good choice for you.
Love this place, spicy food. Make sure to order the dishes from the 2nd half of the menu for authentic Chongqing / Sichuan cuisine
Very tasty food at reasonable prices. Ordered 9 dishes and tea for 9 pax and bill was €119, best value meal I had in whole Europe! Service was friendly and quick and free flow of steamy rice.
The food was very tasty portions could have been a little bigger but for the price I can really recommend this restaurant

Not a bad Chinese restaurant. It is really close to the Marriott which I stayed at.
I ordered the wanton soup which was good, but lacked a bit of depth in flavor.
The Mapo dofu was not made in the traditional, with ma and la but was very tasty. I ended up eating everything.
At the end they provided a plum shot which helped settle the stomach. I also got Jasmin tea which was very nice.
The menu is in German and the waitress speaks very little English but was very nice. They also take credit cards which is a plus in Germany

This place a MUST GO!!! I’m picky about my Chinese food, but hands down, the best. Dishes are not oily, very reasonable prices, and the fried rice was excellent! Duck was amazing and even the stir fried shrimp was prefect, not salty or over seasoned, a must go! The have an English menu and waitress does speak English. Thank you!

I loved this place. It is fine dining. It's clean and service is very good. I went there with my man and we ordered plate for two. This "package" was great. The duck was done beautifully, king paws just delicious, fish and chicken amazing. I loved springroll because it is a homemade one and not from the shop. And for dessert we got fried bananas and fried ice-cream. We loved it and we will definitely be coming back 🌸
Great Chinese food! Although we did not have a reservation, they arranged a table for the 9 of us. We really enjoyed our meals!

Rare and delicious Cantonese treat.

The dishes are simple and carefully constructed. Ingredients are fresh and fragrant. Perfect place to taste and share so many delicious Cantonese specialties.

My favorites were the chili prawns with cashews and the eggplant with beef. The garlic & ginger kissed Water Spinach was also a delicious addition to the meal. Everything was delicious and arrived to the table as soon as it was finished, hot and fresh. No two dishes shared the same, generic sauce like so many bland Imbiss spots in Stuttgart.

The service was wonderful and the availability of underground parking is convenient for a lunch stop.

Great food, great price, and VERY friendly staff. We tried the sweet and sour pork, Sichuan beef, meat sampler, vegetable spring rolls, and prawns with glass noodles.  Fantastic! They were patient with our family of 4 (12 year old and 6 year old), our questions, and spoke great English too!  We will be back.

Stuttgart for years has largely been a wasteland if you love Chinese food. But not anymore!

I'm not an expert in Hong Kong cuisine (outside of dim sum) but after 1 visit I'm really impressed and can't wait to come back and work my way down the menu!

My husband had the Hong Kong Duck, and I had the Chili tofu (basically salt & pepper preparation) and we also got 拍黄瓜 (smacked cucumber salad). I'm not a huge fan of duck in general but my husband is and he loved it, and I thought it was cooked beautifully. The tofu was flavorful and the salad perfectly balanced and addictive.

The service was very nice and quick, and at least one server spoke great English to us. Highly recommend!

2 visits in 3 days (lunch then dinner) to check out this new Cantonese/Hong Kong restaurant. We were delighted to finally be able to eat Cantonese food in Stuttgart, though it was a pity they didn’t offer dim sum. Thus far we found the sweet and sour pork and the 干炒牛河pretty up to par, the pork rib claypot rice was better than the chicken claypot rice. The roast duck was not too bad, just had too many bones. The Gongbao prawn was a tad too salty. They were short handed so the service was really slow, so do not be in a hurry when you dine there. The owners were friendly and it was a pleasure to be able to converse in Cantonese with them. Looking forward to trying out more dishes on the menu.

As a Korean, I went to many Asian restaurants in Germany. I rate this place as the top one. The use of spices and ingredients are perfect, and portion is big. The table and silverware are clean and I loved when chef was checking in for the feedback. I strongly recommend Mapo-Tofu (#47, Tofu pork hot) if you can eat some hot & spicy foods.
Amazing hotdog place one of the best ones I've had. And it's Halal!
Very good and so tasty ❤️❤️❤️
Very friendly staff and nice service. I highly recommend!
I really think the workers and the boss are doing their job very well. The food is very good and is always delivered as quickly as possible.

We ordered 50 burgers for a corporate event. Even though the delivery point was a bit further away, the burgers came on time and they were still warm! It also tasted very good to us. The ordering and payment process was also very simple and always close to the customer. Gladly again in the future!

editorial_summary.overview: Well-known fast-food chain serving grilled burgers, fries & shakes, plus breakfast.

reviews.text:
eat one burger here and your stomach will hate you for days

Years ago you could taste a grilled burger, now even my dog don't touch it.
Good place to have a lunch it’s ok the same flavors
Great food but only takeaway
Check you orders. Got the wrong burger, realized it when got to the car which was parked very far.
Rude customer service. I was charged with 60 cents to pack a 3euro worth dessert! Found it strange when the place only gives takeaways

Hamburgers were *just* patty & a bit of ketchup, fries are way too salted.
"Star Burger" was fine.
price is okay.
Amazing food, in my opinion better than other fast food restaurants.
Pretty average greasy food. Wouldn’t go there again.
Fry chicken downtown Esslingen fast food

editorial_summary.overview: Classic, long-running fast-food chain known for its burgers & fries.

reviews.text:
While I do applaud the choice to hire staff with obvious cognitive disabilities, this does however also negatively impact the quality of the service. Alas, very few people these days actually have to work for minimum wage, so I guess one has to settle for those with an atrophied prefrontal cortex.
But in all sincerity, you shouldn't hire a cashier who can't tell the difference between glass and plastic.
The food and ambience is nice. Best thing washroom is for free 🤩

I have to say, after my recent visit to this particular McDonald's location, I am extremely disappointed with the quality of the food. In fact, I must say it was possibly the worst McDonald's experience I have ever had. The burgers were incredibly tasteless, and to make matters worse, the patties themselves were cold and completely lacking in flavor. It was as if they had been sitting out for hours before being served. Even the salad, which one might expect to be a refreshing and healthy option, was not up to par. The lettuce was wilted and the vegetables were far from fresh.

Overall, I cannot recommend this McDonald's location to anyone who is looking for a satisfying and enjoyable fast food experience. The food is simply not up to the standards that one would expect from this iconic chain. If you are in the area and looking for a quick bite to eat, I would strongly suggest looking elsewhere. There are plenty of other fast food options that offer better quality and more flavorful food.
This particular McDonald's is in a very busy location. I'm not blaming the staff  but I've given up and left 50% of the time because the lines and wait time are too long.
Old style but serves everything a modern McDonald's would

Considering the price range, the Burgers are really good. The staff Always friendly.
I have not eaten there but I could imagine that it will be any different experience

This burger joint is a hidden gem for budget-conscious foodies. The burgers are flavorful, the portions generous, and the prices unbeatable. The service is top-notch, creating a delightful dining experience. If you love tasty burgers without breaking the bank, this place is a must-visit!
Pretty good burgers at an amazing price. If you're in the area looking for burger, definitely go here. Even if you're not in the area, go here -it is quite good.
I ate Currywurst normal and it’s super lecker!  The service is fast and the staffs are also humble! Love it 💕
Really tasty burger, surprisingly good prices!
Such a nice place to visit. The space is not the big but have a table for 6people too. Baguette taste super good, that is hard to find in germany.

Why did I wait so long?? Really enjoyed the food and the atmosphere. I went for lunch and was so pleasantly surprised by my salad - so fresh and delicious. Great service and very reasonable prices. I learned about the monthly wine probieren and cannot wait to try one. What a great, cozy neighborhood spot!!!
Nice french restaurant with good food and wine! Would definitely come back

A gang of friends and I had a wine tasting and meal here this week and it was so wonderful. Dominique the owner and his staff were so nice and made the evening so enjoyable with their fantastic foods and great wine selection. The restaurant also has a small deli with all fresh French cheeses, meats, and take away treats! I highly recommend it if you are craving French! Enjoy
Nice place with friendly staff. If you want to try the good quality French food, here is a good option 😋 the baguette,  creme brulee and the white aperitif are must to try !

editorial_summary.overview: Innovative French bistro fare & fine wines presented in a warm atmosphere with sidewalk seats.

reviews.text: Love this French restaurant. Super friendly staff, great food and very friendly and extensive (when you ask) wine recommendation. Highly recommended place and I will come back again soon!

3 or 4 course menu with multiple options for each course and an eye for wine pairings. We had wonderful food and service.
FYI - they only accept cash or Mastercard (not Visa)

we were 12 People nevertheless the Service was quick and friendly with good advice for every Person at the table. the recommended menu of the day is a good choice because it is well balanced and the wine Pairing is well Chosen. so not a Michelin star Restaurant but a very good Location. recommend

Very very good French Restaurant. I had the menu of the day with the wine Pairing. I was a Little skeptish of the wine pairing as with a first taste to some glasses, the wine was not my favorite. However, when consumed with the course, the wine was paired perfectly. Every dish was amazing. All ingredients are high Quality with good Prices. I would highly recommend this Restaurant to anyone who would want to eat French Food. Service was also very friendly and competent. I would definitely come back here again.

Ask the chef for the wine that goes best with your courses, as he knows what is in his cellar.  Amazing recipes even for "standard"-dishes.  They work on spices, texture,...  and they do it really well.
The only restaurant I know in a 5* hotel without a proper wine list. Missing table cloth. Awful bread. Super irritating! Polite and apologetic staff. The place has seen much better time. Avoid.

There were three of us today at the wonderful Easter Sunday brunch at Le Meridien/LeCassoulet. Many thanks for the uncomplicated reservation! The buffet was terrific and delicious! Thank you very much - we will be happy to be there more often!

We were at branching. The ambience is very upscale, as is the food and drink selection. However, you can drink as much mineral water, coffee specialties and sparkling wine as you want. Admission after table reservation is punctually at 12 p.m. and ends at 3 p.m. The selection of dishes is qualitatively only the best and a very large selection from breakfast to lunch and dessert. The staff is young and very friendly and attentive. We felt very comfortable. And we ate like kings. Say hello to Waltraud Kugler

Every Friday evening there is a French buffet with a large selection of starters, main courses and desserts for €42. Even oysters are on offer.
Unfortunately, the overall quality has declined somewhat over the last few years. The staff is very courteous and always friendly.

Ladies and Gentlemen
On the internet it said lunch on Saturdays from 12 noon. I went there with my son... everything was "closed" - no one knew about it!
Then I was sent up to another restaurant..... "La...." upstairs everything was closed again...!
We went to the reception. The Lord then just said, "...yes, we just found out about that!" And gave me a parking garage ticket with no apology.
I tried to drive it out... Ticket not valid....
So had to go back in, to the reception. There a very nice man took care of me and gave me a valid ticket!

I'm just disappointed by such a posh hotel and such high gastronomy... I only give one star because the nice man helped me!

Greetings from Hosenthien
Great atmosphere and friendly waitress. We ordered dessert and a small snack with salad, both of which were okay :) It’s best for social events perhaps

This place is great. We stopped here to sit outside and have a drink. We ended up going inside and having dinner because the staff is friendly and wanted to give their food a try. Great good. Definitely recommend..

If you give value for your money, you should just pass away from this place. That was one of the most disgusting foods I ever ate in my life. There was hair on my salad and the galette was terrible. I don't how this place got an allowance to sell food.
The coffee here is the style I like, rich coffee taste. The crepe is fine, and would be great if the chocolate cream can be Nutella 😘

Service was attentive even though they were packed during the French game. Flammkuchen crust was fantastic. Prices were very reasonable. And the menu in English, while not expected, was appreciated. Will bring my wife back for a proper dinner and may bump this up to five stars.
Yummy. Purely. Nice warm atmosphere.

The only place to eat French food in Stuttgart.
Really good food, wonderfully presented and served, afterwards you can buy some cheese and other French goodies to extend the wonderful experience.
Looking forward to going again.

We were greeted by a super friendly host who told us although the wait may be an hour (understandably so) we could sit at the bar. We were in a hurry so we agreed.

Our server was super helpful, and he was even manning the whole place by himself. Seriously. Every single table in there, he was their server, but still provided exceptional service and helped us with whatever we needed (hey, we were newbies - had a bunch of questions regarding their specials).
Great food
If you want to enjoy fine dining, this is the place for you during your lunch break. Daily changing lunch menu at reasonable prices based on quality and service .... conclusion delicious 😋

The changing lunch menu is excellent, it's worth getting there early to make sure there's still something left. Even when there were no more dishes, the friendly lady quickly put together some baguettes and toppings for us. The service and advice on the wines, cheese and sausage is extremely helpful and courteous and goes well with the wonderful French specialties.

We come as often as we can.

reviews.text: Simply incredible! A very unique restaurant. Be advised: cash only! Georgian wine is delicious and the food is really high quality. Staff are super friendly and helpful. Obviously you go for the khachapuri but it seems like every item on the menu would be delicious. On the expensive side but worth every penny!
A real Georgian restaurant with rich, delicious, authentic food. Highly recommended for any Georgian food lovers. Put attention - it’s open only after 17:00 and reservation is needed

Very good food and the staff is excellent. You can tell that they're genuinely nice. We had a menu for 2p to get started with Georgian food and it was marvellous.
The picture shows a main dish with chicken.
Will come again.

First time tried the Georgia cousine. I was actually quite satisfied. Overall I like the food and atmosphere there.

I like the Ostri vom Rind. It’s really tasty.
Khinkhali tasted ok. But Appetizer plate from my perspective is way too expensive though.

I went there yesterday with my husband and our little daughter. All three of us loved the place! Very good atmosphere, tasty food and friendly staff! As a Georgian myself, I can confirm that the food and atmosphere is very authentic

editorial_summary.overview: Roast meats & schnitzels, plus breakfasts, in a huge, wood-clad locale overlooking the Schlossplatz.

reviews.text: Food was good and quite quick. The waitress was nice. Have service mind. If you want to sit indoor zone should walk into the restaurant. Sometime you see many people waiting in queue outside but actually indoor zone have available table. But indoor zone quite loud.

THIS PLACE IS A SUPER MUST GO TO EAT WHEN IN TOWN. A***. Was here on 16/10/22. After wandering around town with my friends sights became familiar, whilst trying to get a table on the square. I knew this place to be just the other side of the square from a visit in 2016. The place is always buzzing and I’ve never had a problem getting a table I’m always with at least 10 people. The service is second to none, friendly, polite and knowledgeable on all that is on their menu. I’m a cocktail lover and they do not fail to please even though as you would expect beer is the main thing. And that is in plenty supply in whatever volume you want it. Now the food is ridiculously delicious, like I don’t think I’ve eaten something I’ve ordered or suggested to someone and not watched us melt into the chair in every bite. Crispy ham hock, pork roast, wiener snitzel. There is a phone charger locker if the portable ones are all in use. I seriously highly recommend this place.  In summer be warned but it worth the wait. Go now. Can’t wait

I think the food here is quite average, so is the service. Nothing stood out or is particularly memorable for me.

Despite a mediocre meal, I was still asked by the waiter for a tip. I declined politely and he took the table cloth to swipe the food remains onto me 👎

We went there on aTuesday evening. The place was fully packed ( we had a reservation). We were welcomed by a very friendly staff who tried their best to accommodate our wishes. Inspite of the place being full their was no delay with the service. The food was really great in terms of quantity and quality. Considering the type of crowd that visits the place and the location the high prices are justified. Would definitely love to visit this place again. Highly recommended !!

A central location, very clean. Good atmosphere, very busy. Varied menu with great food. Friendly, helpful staff. Service was quick considering it was busy. We shared a table to get seated sooner, not a problem for us

reviews.text:
Hiked the park and right un the middle was this great resting spot. Although we just had a little treat, there is a full restaurant options. I spied on the plates of other patrons and the food looked and smelled fabulous. It was a holiday weekend and the place was packed, however it was very efficient and we only waited in line for only 3-4 min. There was seating up on a deck around the building as well as inside seating and out in the yard surrounding. So never a concern as to finding a place to sit down and enjoy your treat!
Bathrooms were plentiful,  there was a line for the women's, but it went quickly for as busy as it was.
The park walk was splendid, even for early spring I found some blooms and a very interesting water foul that I have never seen in the states!

Love that place. They have such a great variety of meals, drinks & yummy Kuchen! The surroundings are so beautiful, and they have lots of inside and outside seating options. Also, it can get very busy on a sunny weekend day, but the kitchen works fast.

Mushrooms (100% canned, not fresh) texture like rubber, noodles way overcooked and falling apart. Also the food is 100% re-heated not freshly cooked since it was ready after 1 minute?! Definitely way overpriced for 15€. Additionally the cashier was rude in explaining how the process of getting your food works. Wouldn’t come again for a meal. The cake looks good though.

I absolutely love this place. The walk through the woods to get there, the river and the view make a great day out. The restaurant serves very good food, the service is excellent and fair prices. If you love the nature and eating outside you should visit this place.

Wonderful spot to hike or bike, and then stop for a good lunch and beer. If you want a lazy weekend stroll or even just a breath of fresh air, the trails leading here are gorgeous and the staff is very friendly.

editorial_summary.overview: Expansive restaurant offering traditional Swabian plates, a relaxed bar & al fresco dining.

reviews.text: Classy but laid-back place for German food. Good choices for vegetarians and vegans in addition to the whole selection of meat dishes. We arrived as a party of 10 and they pushed together some tables on the second level patio to accommodate us. Service was polite and the food came out very quickly considering what a large group we were. The menu items came with English descriptions and the staff all spoke English. I had the Dinkelbratlinge, a vegetarian dish of veggie patties with potato salad, cooked carrots, and sour cream. The patties were tasty and had a nice texture. The potato salad looked plain but the dressing was nice and tangy, and not too heavy. All very satisfying. I also had a delightful Vanilla Iced Coffee. My total for the above plus a large mineral water, including 10% gratuity, was about $31,50. This would be on the expensive side back home but I’m not used to prices here yet so I won’t comment. I will say it was good quality food and quite filling, plus nice atmosphere, which are the things that justify a higher price for me.

This place saved us on the 1st of May serving us outstanding breakfast, when almost everything else was closed.
The breakfast was fresh, tasty and full of flavors. Nice idea with serving breakfast in the glass :)
Big plus for friendly and professional staff.

Typical German restaurant. Now I understand why they have the 1/2 Haxe on the menu as the whole one is just huge! One for the professional or hungry eaters I would say. Staff was very friendly and accommodating. Whenever back in Stutgart worth to visit again. Thank you.

Great food and drinks, good service, and an unforgettable atmosphere right in front of this place every night. You'll undoubtedly see a bunch of people gathering and drinking right in front of the entrance of this place, and it creates an amazing vibe. Our Greek waiter Constantin was very friendly and helpful. The drinks were pretty good, even though they were a bit pricey compared to other places nearby, but the location and view from the second floor terrace certainly made up for it.

A whistle stop experience in this totally gorgeous restaurant.
We ordered from Australia, got off the train, which was late!.
Our totally delicious dinner was there on arrival, Pork Knuckle being the main attraction.
We had to run back to the train, full but very happy.
The staff were so friendly and efficient with such a unusual worldwind table!
Highly recommend.

editorial_summary.overview: Dumplings, roast meats & robust local dishes, plus global wines, at a low-lit inn with wooden beams.

reviews.text:
Tricky to find a table without a reservation but was kindly seated at the bar with all outside tables reserved.

Wiener Schnitzel was excellent, as was the service and drinks.

Highly recommended!

We ordered way too much food and drinks (wink). Make sure to get your reservation in early if you plan to dine during the weekend. Beef tar tar was great and Lamb came with this cornbread type thing. Don’t know what it was but it was amazing. We also shared this beet pickled salmon which was refreshing. The restaurant has a wine guy that’ll set you up a nice wine to compliment your meal.

We were very much looking forward to dining here after reading the reviews and Michelin accolades. The space is cozy and great for a date night, or for a nice dinner with friends or colleagues. I was underwhelmed by the seasoning of the food as much as I wanted to love it, the dessert was the best part.

We had reservations and were immediately seated. I started with the Asian pork belly and spicy kohlrabi kimchi. The kimchi was very good and had a nice kick, but the pork belly was lacking much flavor, even with all the sauce. I then had the zwiebelrostbraten with spätzle. The steak was cooked perfectly and tender, but I still found it lacking much flavor. The onions were full of flavor and took over the dish, but seasoning outside of that was minimal. The spätzle did taste like it had the nutmeg in it and was cooked perfectly.

Split the chocolate dish for dessert and it made the whole night better. The mouse portion was so creamy and delicious, while the brownie was warm and just melted in your mouth. The ice cream had some type of crunchy chocolate as well. The strawberry and rhubarb were both nice additions, as was the mint cream.
Both food and service were great. White asparagus in May was especially super.

My wife and I celebrated our 23rd anniversary here.  I had a lamb dish that was excellent.  They have a very good wine selection. On the downside, my wife was not impressed with the chocolate mousse. Overall, we had an enjoyable outing.

Wonderful experience trying this new restaurant here in Sindelfingen. Fantastic massive menu with lots of choices, especially for vegetarians.

House specialties including spanakopita and moussaka 😋 yum!

We enjoyed the Calamari, Fresh Pita with Olive spread and Eggplant stuffed with feta. Everything was flavorful and colorful. For those meat eaters we watched as huge platters of gyro passed by with fresh vegetables too.

Service was great and restaurant was busy on a Sunday night. You can order through Lieferando as well. We didn’t make reservations which was risky.

We showed proof of vaccination and wore masks 😷 til we got to the table.
!!! Need for greek??? You will experience here the real taste. With family,friends or just a date you have to try this kitchen. Prices are fair, employees really friendly ☺️
Great Hellenic restaurant with great prices!

The food was absolutely wonderful. Fresh sea food and excellent gyros, souvlaki, and other meats. Literally everything we had was cooked to perfection. The server was very friendly and on top of everything. The location is perfect for dinner, right off the road, and the outdoor seating is so relaxing. This is by far the best Greek food in town hands down.

Best Greek food I’ve had in town. Definitely going to be our new regular spot. Sea food was fresh and meats were seasoned very well. It doesn’t get any better than this place and the prices are very reasonable when compared to the portions.

editorial_summary.overview: Grilled meats & meze platters in a relaxed, family-run venue with courtyard seating.

reviews.text:
Excellent Restaurant!
We found this restaurant by coincidence whilst driving by and thought to give it a try and we definitely didn't regret it.
The staff was very friendly, professional and the service fast.
We shared a few starters and mains and everything we had was really delicious. We were really happy we tried this place. As far as I know they also have live greek music on some evenings so I would love to go when they have it.
I would recommend to reserve a table before though.
I would definitely recommend this Restaurant and we will definitely visit again when in town.

Staff were very friendly but not a great choice on the menu.
The mixed starters platter for 10euro per person was fried aubergine and fried courgette with some cream cheeses. I expected better.
The mains came with Pommes, I requested vegetables instead but was told that wasn't possible. A little disappointing.
Delicious greek food in Stuttgart. It is an amazing place where you can enjoy of greek food and nice atmosphere with your friends.

super chilled in the backyard, mama in the kitchen does a great job. good service too and reasonable prices. especially the starter with feta and tomatoes + the filled calamaris been standing out. not like the other dishes haven't been great ^

One of the best places in the area, with delicious greek food and friendly staff
Fyi: Might be full in the evenings, you should make a reservation.

We visited in May last year, just after the curfew ended and it was really nice. The place looks modern, elegant and the staff is friendly and helpful. We had Mousaka, Arnaki Fileto - Lammfilet with Thymian Kartoffeln (was great) and The Greek Taste Soufflé (only minus that the fruits were frozen, not fresh). Value for money 4 ⭐️
Very nice place! Very nice stuff! Delicious food! 5 star recommendation ☺️
Top place, mellow food and friendly service. We will definitely come back here!
I’ve been here twice and I really like this restaurant. It looks very beautiful and the food is great.

Really enjoyed my stay in this restaurant. The service was very friendly and the food was delicious as well as fairly priced for being a Greek restaurant. The meat was of high quality, but we especially enjoyed the appetizers.

editorial_summary.overview: Casual eatery with a patio for small plates, seafood & classic Greek dishes, plus grilled options.

reviews.text:
The food was delicious. The service and atmosphere is top. I recommend this restaurant for sure, Greek experience with tipical music.
I ate the calamar with chickpeas pure (that could be a bit more quantity).

We were walking around downtown and happened upon this place. Decided to try as we don’t find Greek cuisine very often. This place was delicious! Not only were staff very friendly and warm, but the food is very tasty and delectable. We loved everything we ordered. I know pommes can be monotonous in taste but these pommes had lovely hint of Greek seasoning, lovely light crispiness and fluffiness at the same time- just delicious! The dessert was amazing as well. We will definitely be coming back here soon 🧡🧡💚

Edit: Needed to mention this, the food is cooked from scratch and made fresh. Nothing is pre-made and reheated so the wait time from food to table will be a wait longer than usual but that is how you know there is a chef that is compassionate and cooks with love and wants to put forth quality food.

Good beer and good food. I’d recommend the platters that come with rice and veggies or order a bunch of dishes and share family style. I went with one other person and left a bit unsatisfied because the octopus only comes with onions and mushy peas, would have liked a carbohydrate like rice or potatoes with it, however this is indicated in the menu so I can’t complain. Great service and the food arrived quickly.

Great absolutely tasteful meal I had here. I ordered a bifteki filled with feta cheese in it. Which I like and is ordered more often at other places as well by me, but this one, together with the perfectly grilled vegetables was outstanding.
But: I think not having one service around directly at the entrance (ground floor) is not handy. This restaurant exists out of more dining rooms/floors and just one ore two servants is just not enough to cover/overseeing it all. Therefore I had two wait to long before one was coming down to welcome and guiding me to a table (an other waiting couple already turned around and left before the change to make them customers), I had to wait a little long to get my ordered plate and after that I wanted to order an extra side dish, but no chance, cause, yeah, no contact possibilities with a servant, cause simply wasn't there.
Therefore, there are no five stars, but because of the good food, there are still four.

Consider the best Greek food you can find in Germany.
They have 2 different menus, German and English. The seating is good, bright and good sunlight. There are 2 floors.

The grill dishes and octopus are just like what you will get in Greece.

You can make a reservation before your visit.

editorial_summary.overview: Charming, petite restaurant dishing up traditional Greek meze, seafood & meat dishes, plus drinks.

reviews.text:
We enjoyed a lot during the time we spent there. The ambiance was very nice 👍🏼 and service was very quick and good.
Prices are reasonable compared to other restaurants.

Greek cuisine, indoor and outdoor seating not so far from the city center. The location is prime if you want to head to the city centre afterwards. Safe is friendly and accommodating. The food is plentiful and quickly delivered.
The portions are huge and anything you order will be a feast regardless of the price. In comparison to the original one in Bad Canstatt, there isn’t much of a difference besides the outdoor seating and the set up of the building structure.
We give this experience a five out of five.

Great good with good vibes and easy to adore!
Authentic Greek cuisine easily accessible from Olgaeck U-Bahn Station. Place is cozy and can be very busy during dinner. Price is reasonable.

Excellent Food 👌🏼
Great People 👍🏽
Bit chaotic but authentic 😁
Great place to share the food with friends ab family 🤝
Greek Tapas 💚

Lovely Mediterranean restaurant, i would say it greek themed and styled but adjusted to Germany.
The food was excellent, good portions, tasty, reasonably priced, kind service.
Visited already several times and would definitely come back again.

editorial_summary.overview: Bright, contemporary Greek spot with a terrace & a festive vibe in the evening, plus occasional DJs.

reviews.text: Food and service excellent, unfortunately very crowded, but that makes sense considering how good it is.

Food was good and friendly and hard working staff. We’ve had a company event with around 50 people here. This would have been a 4-Star rating. Two stars are removed because of the very impolite behaviour of the owner who turned on the music so loud, that it was not possible to talk to each other anymore. This happened on our last event also. He ruined the nice evening as the group dissolved quickly.

We used to like this place but things have totally changed. the waiters were totally rude, disrespectful especially towards women. We felt totally insane. We got shouted at for now reason and are still in shock about what went down this night. Never again!

Great Greek food, turns into a club and people start to dance on the tables and throw paper napkins. Unfortunately only problem is that its difficult to get a group reservation which shows how popular this place is!
Stuttgart Expat Meetups members like to meet here in small groups

Food was really good we booked as a group from our office
Starters were of great variety and we liked it
Vegetarian main course can be improved
Dessert was yogurt honey kinda different

Meze Meze.adr_address: Ob. Waiblinger Str. 110, 70374 Stuttgart, Germany
Meze Meze.name: Meze Meze

reviews.text: MAKE A RESERVATION. We went at 19:30 on a Wednesday and there were people waiting for tables. It’s very popular. As we were a couple, we opted for the €50 meat special for two. SO. MUCH. FOOD. We were not disappointed. I had wanted to order the fried cheese, but the waiter urged me to wait to see how much food came with the menu. His recommendation was spot on. We could not finish all the wonderful food that arrived. Everything was very fresh & presented beautifully. One of the best Greek meals I’ve enjoyed in Stuttgart. They offer menus in Greek, German & English. The waiter was very friendly & explained the menu well. We will definitely eat here again & would love to try the fish menu. All of the fish we saw being served looked equally delicious!

Greek Cuisine: Authentic place to go eat for Tapas greek plates.. This is the original (1) restaurant # 2 is located downtown. There is a lot of outdoor space for seating for groups of guess.
We give this experience a 4 out 5 because the service is subpar, when it get busy… you can get lost in the pecking order.. However, the quality of the food is closer to a 5.

amazing place, very good price, great food, housewine white wine also excellent. very fast of food providing, grilled octopus, ganelen, fried sardellen is just as fresh like portugal beach... waiters are very friendly. my  number one restaurant in Stuttgart!
Great food, good prices and fantastic music! Loved the atmosphere
Very good!

I had a Gyros there! It was very delicious! Respect..!!!  The food is excellent, and the people are so friendly!!  Next time I'm in town, i will make this my first stop! They make excellent Greek food, and fresh from the grill!! Einfach Lecker!!!
It is an accurte Greek Food reataurant
Top

The gyros is really tasty and I recommend it! The ambience is that of a fast food restaurant and it looks accordingly.
I'd love to come back.

editorial_summary.overview: Spicy meat curries, biryani & vegetarian choices, plus a lunch buffet, in a relaxed, bright space.

reviews.text: The location of the restaurant is great and the ambiance is inviting and comfortable. I ordered the paneer tikka tandoori, nan, and paneer chilli, and they were all incredible. The paneer tikka, in particular, was exceptional and presented beautifully in a sizzler plate. Although it's on the pricier side, the staff and service were excellent. Overall, I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a delicious meal and a memorable dining experience.

Typical Indian mentality. Had been here twice. First time with Indian colleagues, second time with my German colleagues. I could see the difference in the serving. First time, there wasn’t even a smile. The second time it was a complete turnaround. Wishing us, all smiles and energetic. Nonetheless, the food was good. Nan is a little thick. Maybe they need to work on that. The gravy is priced at €12-€14, but quantity suffices only for 2 pieces of nan or roti. The lassi was superb. Do try it.
Food is authentic. Good quality dishes. Definitely recommend Thalis and Lassi
We had our dinner here, you can sit inside and outside to enjoy your food. Vegetarian options are great. Mango lassi is really yummy.
The food was tasty but service could be better. The ambience could be more authentic

Was here for the weekday lunch Buffet in 2019. The staff were very kind and friendly. The buffet options were also slightly more than other similar buffets. The food also tasted good and was served hot and fresh. There

The food was nice but i missed something when I tried the menus. The lassi was tasty though.
Tried the veg mixed starter but didn't get any dips to try with. Karahi paneer was good but not really tasty.

Service was good though. The atmosphere was not really great, its a bit cramped inside the restaurant since the table were assigned too close to each other.

Very friendly staff. Run by tamil speaking Srilankans. Food was not tasty. Plus I found an aluminium metal piece in my food. I was about to swallow but then I pulled it out of my mouth. Had it gone in I should have gone to Emergency in Hospital. Very careless preparation of food. Was a big health risk for me.

Went to this place for a quick lunch after checking google reviews. Needless to say we weren't disappointed. We ordered dal makhni, 2 of the paneer dishes and garlic naan. Food was delicious and authentic Indian food. Loved everything about our meal.

Food and service were excellent. Prices were very reasonable. The server was very helpful in selecting something that we'd like out of the vast menu. Be warned that there didn't seem to be any A/C so it was a little warm. Other than that, I'd highly recommend it.

#1 for family and friends gathering occations. Staff is friendly and the food is really great!
They also take into consideration about customization (spice levels and vegeterian options).

Been there twice. Quite a mixed experience I would say. Almost had the same menu both of the times. Food is overall good. I’d give 7/10, it has Indian taste but not like what you’ve already had in India or something. Something was missing. The naan was also not that smooth. Ordered pakoras and it came with broccoli and zucchini stuffed.  Would never expect that. Servicing could be done bit more friendlier too. Specially the guy. Ok price for the type of food. Lassi is good, must try. In general 7,5\10

One of the best Indian food we have sampled so far in Stuttgart! They have quite a good collection of starters (indian kebabs) served on a sizzling hot plate, we had the chicken hara tikka and loved the minty flavour and overall composition. Their curries with naan are also very tasty - we had mutton curry and liked it quite a lot. Make sure to specify you would like Indian spicy if you want the dishes prepared traditionally and can handle the spice levels. To drink we had the sweet lassi and mango lassi, the mango lassi was more tasty. We finished off with kulfi for dessert and it was a lovely homemade mango ice cream with almond and raisin toppings. We really liked this place and would definitely go back there. We went there on a Tuesday evening and got a table easily without reservations. The service was a little slow, but the food was definitely worth the wait.
Excellent quality food and awesome ration quality price. The service was quite fast and the serving lady was really welcoming and very polite. I definitely recommend this place to try out.

I walk by this location almost everyday but never gave it a try. Since it was open I gave it a shot

Service
It wasn't that packed but the service was pretty decent and didn't have any issues.

Food
I ordered the Alu Naan, Chicken Tikka Masala (spicy), and a Mango Lassi. The Mango Lassi was pretty good with the Mago and yogurt creaminess. The Chicken Tikka Masala was heavily seasoned with seasonings where it almost tasted like chili. The Alu Naan was hot and fresh but barely any flavor. Also the rice with the Masala was cold.

Overall
Compared to other Indian Restaurants in the area this place is average or ok at best.
Customer friendly staff. Very nice ambience. Good taste.

Gone are the days when I would recommend as the top one for Indian food specially when ordering online. Ordered 4 dishes and 2 of them had like close to half the quantity of what it should be. Also the prices were raised recently.
Checkout the pic showing the quantity we received in two out of 4 dishes.

Edit: Writing a reply for your "polite" reply. I've seen you raising cost just within a month, so please don't talk about 10 years. Secondly, you are not even sorry as you didn't even wish to look into it if the order was for today or not. It was a couple of days back. Same packing but two items are almost half way down and talking about the reason as ability to pack properly?

Great food. We have been there for the lunch buffet (all you can eat) for 8,90 EUR.
Incl. great variety of vegetable dishes, one chicken  (Halal) meal, fried vegetables. Mixed salads with different sauces, naan bread and lassi for desert. They serve Dinkelacker beer.
Staff is really very friendly.
It's a good Indian restaurant. But the roti are very thick. The quantity of vegetables served is less. If 2 people are there then they need to order 2 dishes.

The food is wonderful! I've ordered three times now.

Two out of the three times the food has been at least 45 minutes late so make sure not to order online at busy times. Even though they said 55 minutes waiting time at 19:00 this evening, my food came at 20:55. That's nearly a two hour wait. And I live a 3 minute drive away.
The host was really warm and welcoming.  We thoroughly enjoyed the food. Strongly recommended if you are looking for some authentic Indian food.

I don’t mind poor service as long as the food is good, but our meals were not good at all. We had chicken korma and some tikka dishes, but they did not taste good. The server also made a face and hesitated when someone at our table wanted tap water. The food took a long time to make, so I thought it would be decent, but alas it was not. The basmati rice was good though if that’s a consolation!
Wonderful variety of dishes on the menu.  Fantastic service!  Fair prices.

We heard good things of this Indian restaurant and ordered our go-to dish Chicken Tikaka Masala for takeout. It was absolutely delicious and well spiced. Sometimes it is too spicy, then not spicy at all, but at Roshni's it tastes just right.

The inside was clean and nicely decorated when we where there. The waitress was also super friendly.

We will definitely come back and dine in the next time.

We visited Roshni’s palace today evening and had Keema Naan and Mutton vindalo!! The taste was pretty good. Naan was so soft and Mutton was so tender. Curry was spicy as expected and it was close to authentic Indian taste. Only problem was the young waiter was so uninviting and unfriendly. That made us uncomfortable and want to leave soon. But there was another punjabi uncle there who was much more friendly

Authentic Indian cuisine. Tried out Mango Lassi, Mix tandoori Platter, Chicken Tikka Tandoori, Kulcha, Butter Naan, Gulab jam. Experience was Chicken Tikka tandoori, butter Naan, Kulcha, Mango lassi very good & tasty. But Mix platter Tandoori was average and Gulab jam was also average because very very very sugary.
Very clean Restaurant. Underground Parking available. Also compatible to visit along with babies.
Amazing taste and fast service. Very authentic Indian food. Highly recommend!

Good Indian flavour in the vicinity.
Perfect ambience with different type of Hindu Gods.
Ordered paneer curry and stuffed kulcha. Liked it.

Recommended for all.
Absolutely amazing food. Definitely authentic. Service was excellent. I'd give it 10 stars if I could. Highly recommend.
Biriyani is not up to the mark but Tandoori chicken, garlic naan and mutton gravy, chicken gravy were tasty. We really enjoyed having Indian dishes in this restaurant.

Great Italian restaurant!
Definitely recommending the fish soup.. it reminded of Italy.
The tuna salad however wasn't as great.
Pizzas were good as well.

One of the best gluten free pizzas I’ve ever had! Had it not been for the clear marking I would’ve never guessed it was gluten free. The restaurant also has a great outdoor terrace, lovely staff and real value!
Very cozy. Delicious food. Nice staff. Good location near the train station. Make a reservation!
Very tasty Bolognese (with the right pasta 😅). Service is also nice.

The chef’s food: obviously 10/10!
And nice staff!

editorial_summary.overview: Fortnightly menus featuring pasta & other Italian specialties, plus fine wines, in an airy locale.

reviews.text: Excellent Italian restaurant, not big menu but outstanding taste. Friendly and elegant environment. Highly recommended. A hidden gem.

The food is very good, yes, my level of home cooking, which is a compliment, but I found the prices extremely high for the small servings here. 3 of us spent over 200€ with wine but decided to go to Vapiano around the corner afterwards for something more substantial
We had a good meal. My only issue was a limited menu. I don't eat seafood; I don't remember if that was the issue.
We enjoyed the food. It wasn't outstanding but good enough that I will come back.
Overrated. Average food, overpriced.

editorial_summary.overview: Traditional Italian cooking with a contemporary twist, served with wine in an elegant dining room.

reviews.text: One of the best restaurants I have been at. Really good food and great service. Definitely will come back there. I highly recommend it.

An authentic Italian place, family-owned by Giovanna and her son Fabio, very welcoming service, best pasta, great wine selection and absolutely the best Panna Cotta - the price value ratio is absolutely justified. Recommend!
The dishes are super delicious. I would suggest for everyone who wants to have delicious experience in every bites.
Fantastic food, service and atmosphere. Kind staff!

The best Italian restaurant in Stuttgart I would say. Although it’s a bit pricy, it’s Wort it. The dishes are cooked by a real Italian Nonna, what you taste in every bite and the restaurant is a family business. They have always fresh fish, seasonal dishes and lovely starters. The service is excellent.

editorial_summary.overview: Pasta, pizza & typical Italian mains, plus house specials, in a relaxed, pared-down venue.

reviews.text: Super good for foods and wines 😍 service also excellent
Very nice and authentic little Italian restaurant. It is family owned. Price are super fair and food is really good. The restaurant is very small, so a reservation is recommended.
I liked this place a lot. The food is amazing and the waiter Carlo was very nice and friendly. Will visit again :)
Delicious food, especially the tomato soup. Great pizza and lasagna too! Very small, casual, and friendly place.  Highly recommended.

Nice little Italian restaurant situated on a quiet street. The staff was very friendly and helpful with our takeaway order, and the food was tasty with big portions. The garden looked really cosy too, we almost regretted not eating there.

editorial_summary.overview: Aperitifs, antipasti, pasta dishes & pizzas in an understated restaurant/bar.

reviews.text: It’s a nice place for dinner. I liked the pesto fresh pasta and the combination of burrata tomato and the pasta was absolutely perfect. The pizza could be better!

Food was fantastic: I had the tomato soup, homemade pasta and seafood, and the panna cotta dessert. Homemade pasta was fantastic! Wait staff were friendly and responsive. Atmosphere is okay, it is a busy place so don't expect a quiet romantic table to yourself - but most people respect it and are not overly loud. Would recommend for good Italian food.

Superb Italian food in the middle of the city.

This restaurant and bar offers great variety of delicious plates and cocktails.

The staff are friendly and nice.

The place is big, and it has seatings outdoors, and indoors. The interior design is really nice and full of nice touches.

The plates are really delicious, and they bring really tasty bread to the table.

The place is open till late, and you can sit for a drink, a snack or a meal.
They also take card, which is great.

This place is so good, for a place that close to the city center.
