Great restaurant
I ordered pizza and pasta,, they were delicious
guess our fav Italian place downtown. never been disappointed . the pasta fruit di mare is the cracker on the regular menu at least for us 😁 great service too and reasonable prices

editorial_summary.overview: Restaurant serving seasonal Italian dishes in a stylish setting with large windows & sidewalk seats.

reviews.text: We sat outside and the service was prompt and friendly. Honestly, I've never seen a waiter in Germany move so quick. The drinks were super. All dishes were *superb.*

We reserved really late on a Saturday and still got a table. The menu is a little confusing because they have a lot of really nice options for lunch and were unsure if we could also order them for dinner. We asked and we were able to also order from the lunch menu. The dinner was really good. The desserts were also very delicious. The waiter was very nice. Atmosphere very pleasant.
Extremely bad and unpleasant experience. Rude and arrogant stuffs, tasteless food, overpriced. Not recommended at all !!
Food was okay. Ordered salad, tomatoes with mozzarella and something else. Tomatoes were really firm, pale, and not ripe. 🍅

This was my favorite of all dining experiences since being in Stuttgart. The atmosphere was very nice, with white tablecloths and cloth napkins,  which is expected at the price point. The menu available was very well put together and the meal itself was simply divine.  The wine selection was extensive. The staff were excellent. I can honestly say that I never saw the bottom of my glass. There was someone on hand to keep it filled with wine. This is by far the best restuarant that I have dined in. I hope to return very soon.

editorial_summary.overview:
Upscale pasta, pizza & fish dishes served
in a sleek, modern space or at terrace tables.

reviews.text: The food was pretty good. The service was weird. I’m generally not phased by German customer service but this was off even for that. There was a gentleman constantly bussing our table. As soon as we finished with a plate even if we weren’t sure, he was whisking them away. He then got upset with us when we kept trying to get our bill for over half an hour. Maybe his humor didn’t translate but otherwise the food and atmosphere was nice.
Pizza delicious, but service was poor - no one enquired about my meal, if I wanted desert or another drink.

Very comfortable environment to stay, everything is clean and neat!! It wasn’t crowded when we got there around 2-3pm. Staff was really nice and welcoming, the food was great too!!! We ordered clam spaghetti and seafood spaghetti along with some starters, there were all delicious and amazing!!! You could see the cooking process through the kitchen glass window which is quite fun. Recommended!!!
Ok but not great. The Trüffel pasta was ok but the Service on a saturday night was not the best

Food was fine but very rude staff. They just try their best to ignore you even if the restaurant is not crowded at all. They came very late to take out order and then to give us the bill. They hit the plates on the table and if you ask em for sth, they act like you have done sth terrible

This Italian restaurant at the heart of Stuttgart's westend district really drives the beat with a restricted menu but excellent food, the place has an unitalianate feel to it but somehow makes for an interesting athmosphere. It is also reasonably priced.
The pizza were really good ! Nothing more to say :)

Das Essen ist sehr lecker, aber der waiter ist ein bisschen rassistisch.

Edit:
---
First time I ate here: Ordered a Pizza WITHOUT cheese, got a pizza with cheese and the waiter knew it as well (he pointed that out when I was paying) -- still ate it, not gonna throw food away.

Second time: I was yelled at for sitting at a table (that wasn't marked reserved) instead of being politely asked to move to a different one -- like any other guest would.

Third time: Picked up food, asked to pay with card, wanted to include tip, the waiter declined and said it wasn't possible.

Fourth time: Asked to pay with card again, but the waiter said that normally payments with card are only possible starting from €20, so I asked him to bill me the €20 anyways, and the rest is his tip.. he declined.

Fifth time: Carried cash with, the waiter would not accept any tip still.

And so and so, the service never accepting any tip, doing the bare minimum with a hint of snobbishness and disregard to any of my requests.

@the owner: If you'd rather ignore the signs and just say a prayer instead, then be my guest, but my review will be 1 star for failure to deal with racism within your staff.

@the waiter: You've won, I'm not eating here anymore 👍

@the reader: Take everything with a grain of salt, but if you're a person of colour, you might be greeted with a bit of snobbishness and a sprinkle of rudeness, however, you won't have to pay any tip and the food is good ;)
A nice take on Italian food! Very good service, too. Try their daily specials!

I was in Goldoni for a Dinner and the food was fantastic, accompanied from the Italian Wine options and with the super energy from Silvio the Italian owner.

Since this experience all my friends and family went for Dinner there, and we are always impressed how we are so well attended.

Thank you Silvio!

The food is delicious and the staff is very friendly. I’ve been here a couple of times. I recommend to choose something from the daily menu because of the suprisingly good and creative combinations of ingredients, taste and structures. And leave some space for dessert, because you don’t wanna miss that.😊
This was a great experience. The family that owns and operates this make you feel like you're part of it. The food was fantastic.
The best Italian restaurant I have been to by far! Always so friendly and no matter what you order, it'll be delicious.

We had a dinner here and we were cery happy with meals. Its not expensive. Pizza pastry was the best we ever had. Pasta and apetizers are very nice. The only flaw is that the restaurant closes at 21.30h
Great lunch option, if you want decent Italian food and not wait long. I usually get my pizza 5min after ordering it.

editorial_summary.overview: Pizzas, pastas & typical mains, with gluten-free options, in an airy space hung with colorful art.

reviews.text: They needed literally 1h to serve our main dish of pasta, after the appetizer, which is boiled in 90 seconds. The wine was at room temperature so very bad, because the room was at 30 degrees. The food was good but not to wait so much.

The local is really nice and so is the ambiance, and the service. But watch out with the pizzas, since some of them don't come with tomate sauce on them and literally taste like nothing (it wasn't even stated on the menu that they wouldn't be done without). The soup and the pasta were really good tho. But I wouldn't recommend the place.
Their pizza is fantastic! The vegan pizza was better than expected. Normally I'm not one to eat the crust but I hade to with this one. The crust was delicious!!!
Probably the best Italian restaurant in Stuttgart! Friendly staff and excellent food. If you are hungry, ask for the meat platter (not on the menu). Fantastic value for money!

Just had a really nice diner at this restaurant.
As soon as we sat in the place, we already New we would like it.
We were taken care of quickly and professionally. You have a broad choice of courses. The food was really delicious and served pretty quickly (which was an advantage as we were going to the cinema).
I would definitely recommend for a romantic diner, a girls’ night out or a family thing.
Good, friendly service despite being quite busy. My pizza was very good and my buddy said his pasta was tasty as well. Good location to boot.
Nice location, easily accessible and airy in the summer. But staff is super bored and unfriendly, food caused me diarrhea.
The pizza was huge and delicious! The service however was bad. They brought us the wrong drinks and refused to change the beverages, and would not allow splitting the bill.
Nice pizza place in a corner. Great atmosphere.
Very nice ambience, delicious food with authentic Italian flavour. The only little downside for me was no chicken in the menu.

We had dinner there this Friday evening and it somehow was super empty. Probably because of the good weather. Therefore, we got served quickly. The service was friendly and the location overall is neat.
Tiramisu was very good with plenty coating. Lasagna was made with real Bolognese. Carbonara was very tasty, maybe too much garlic but fine for me. Pizza Pane was one of the best I ever had.
It was a nice place, with quite a waiting time. The most strange thing was that waitress didn't know what's the soup of the day.
I like the ambience at Don Via. Food was good and price was reasonable. Service was okay.
Amazing food and the staff was very friendly and nice!

Food is average. I had tortellini with basil pesto.  They definitely don't make the pasta by themselves. The worst part are the very unorganized and unprofessional waiters. First, I had to approach a waiter and wait for some time to get seated. Then, they had discussions in front of the guests. Some of them had an argument and decided to have it over their guests tables. I felt very uncomfortable. Even McDonald employees are better trained...

We had to wait for such a long time, and I have never eaten such a bad pizza!! Couldn’t finish it because all the low quality cheese made me feel sick! Oh and did I mention that the water they put on your table (before you arrive to “eat”) costs 9.50€?!? This is so rude and unacceptable! NEVER going there again!

Pretty location and convenient if you're visiting one of the musicals. Their menu is very basic, we ordered pizza and it was delicious, the pasta not so much. Their drinks are good but their service is very slow.

I would like to give it a 0 star rating but I cannot. Worst service ever, even for Europe. I almost got up and left without paying. Never got my second glass of wine. Service generally ultra slow. Caprese salad had a wired taste. Pizza was tasteless. Should have looked at the reviews before I went too hungry to care.

Poor experience. I'd put zero stars if I could. We're still waiting for our food for 45 minutes, a salad and one spaghetti dish. Bigger table that came after us have already been served and we are only 2 people.

editorial_summary.overview: Homestyle antipasti, pastas & grilled mains in a pared-back dining room or on a sidewalk terrace.

reviews.text: Typical homemade Italian food, with a good atmosphere and very friendly waiters. I will repeat.
Amazing restaurant ! Service by Gino is outstanding. He’s absolutely polite and helped to choose our dishes. Great experience overall
The food is so fresh and delicious. The staff is friendly. The atmosphere is excellent. We will definitely be back!

Very good Italian food
Waiters very kind
I recommend
Love the food!!!! Been here a few times. Consistently delicious!

Roberts cucina italiana.adr_address: Bosch Areal, Breitscheidstraße 4, 70174 Stuttgart, Germany
Roberts cucina italiana.name: Roberts cucina italiana

reviews.text: We had a wonderful time at this place. The food, the drinks and the service were all great! And Limoncello Spritz was something I've never tasted before. It's really worth tasting, especially in such warm weather.

Italian cuisine, elegant indoor seating with a diverse group of parties. Lengthy menu with layers of goodness. Professional staff to the tee.
Food for all eaters by far… one of the best spot in Stuttgart.
Kudos to the owners/ staff!
We give this experience a 5 out 5.
Enjoy!
1st visit and will definitely be back. Wonderful atmosphere and delicious food. The burrata, pizza and panna cotta were outstanding.

Top decoration and ambience for Italian flair.
Staff was respectful, friendly and at all moments attentive to our needs. Food was good, cocktails very enjoyable and prices accessible and accordingly fitting to the variety of options available. Looking forward to a second visit.

The food was tasty, but missed a bit of soul to say it like that, good but a personal touch or a stronger flavour would have made it better! Nice atmosphere and friendly staff!
We definitely enjoed ourselves here!

editorial_summary.overview: Classic Italian pasta & pizza, plus fish & meat dishes, in a busy space with an enclosed patio.

reviews.text: Valle is one of the best, reasonably priced Italian restaurants in all of Stuttgart. The pasta 🍝 is really incredible. You must always go for something on the truffle ‘special’ menu (even though it’s available 90% of the time 🙃). It’s a monthly spot for us!

As a restaurant with friendly staff I recommend this place.
The spaghetti with tomato sauce was just that, not a herb to be seen.
Some Italian pizazz added to each dish would bring Valle up to speed.  Maybe a herb , Oregano or even Chilli grinder would do the trick?

Been there with the family of my wife while they've been on visit in Stuttgart. We didn't know it before and weren't sure about our choice. It was perfect , perfect place to have food with your family or friends nice and cozy atmosphere. The staff is super friendly and so helpful! Special is that the void cares for the customers himself and takes care you enjoy your stay. Five stars already earned, the food is a bonus. Never had that God Italian food out of Italy! Really delicious, nice looking and fresh ingredients.
If possible I would give more than 5 stars. If you're around try it!

Nice Italian restaurant that I can strongly recommend if you're the fan of classic Italian Tomaten soup or Quattro Formaggi. Also we've tryed salad with salmon and shrimps - tastes good, wore over it looks simply wonderful. The prices are reasonable and atmosphere is quite usual - so you can drop in here any time.

Authentic Italian in cosy setting. Make sure you book a table in advance as this place is very popular! Check out their special truffle menu, if you are lucky and definitely order the spaghetti finished in a massive wheel of parmesan... Amazing! Fabulous, attentive staff. Will go back again whenever I'm in Stuttgart.

Music was too loud for dinner time, we couldn't hear each other while sitting at the smallest table. Pizza pastry ok, but not as expected in real italian pizzeria. I appreciate vegan options. Overall it was a  rather pleasant experience.
A top Italian food experience with a nice service. Food is good and plates are generous. I really recommend.

Very good pizza.
Always busy in the weekend but you will not wait long to get a table.
Friendly stuff, and vey good service.
I recommend this place
The tiramisù was not bad considering we are not in Italy and the service quick. They should make also cocktails, they have only few options on the menu.

This is a busy "little" Italian place. We (me and my partner) waited nearly 30minutes to be spoken to and sat; all waiters/waitresses seemed run off their feet. We were surprised however in the speed to get out orders taken and food out; about 25 minutes. The food was good, the pizzas are humongous. They're wider than your hand and forearm. I had spaghetti bolognese, it didn't disappoint.

Sicilian restaurant. Food is ok. They showed us table inside even we intended to sit outsite. I think they thought they can find customer easily for outside. Staff is funny but good people. All Italian ( they speak italian between). Price is moderate, not very expensive. Little bit noisy but we liked the place. The people comes very must for takeaway pizza. Next time, we will insist to sit @ outside table.

Possibly the best Italian restaurant in Stuttgart. The spaghetti crabonara is brilliant & so are the pizzas. It's a quaint place but feels cramped if you visit in large groups. Too many tables squeezed into limited space and the place is often full.

High quality food with great ambient. I loved all the foods, but personally think the pastas and other foods were better than pizzas! That is why I gave 4 stars. Otherewise it deserves definitely 5 stars.

Excellent Italian restaurant in the heart of Stuttgart. The dish of the day was tortelloni with truffle and meat filling. Just delicious. Carbonara was also original Italian and very tasty. Highly recommended

It's a perfect Italian place for dine-in.
The spaghetti is just too delicious.
A must visit place if you are in Feuerbach region!
Friendly staff and lovely atmosphere!
Delicious food and friendly staff!
Ok
Great people you can switch off and have fun. I only saw the food by sight, it looks delicious, next time I'll eat something. Otherwise great people. Really like the store.❤️

Looks very unassuming from the outside. The area inside very small but sufficient. The operator is very friendly and accommodating and the food is excellent! Unfortunately, I'm not from the area, otherwise I would stop by here more often.
Very tasty food, authentic and honest. We recommend!

Today was my first time eating at this restaurant though I’ve been going to the Markthalle for years.  It was for the traditional brother/sister day out that I do with my sister in my trips to Germany. I had the linguine with beef and and she had the penne pasta.  The meal was amazing and I was definitely a member of the clean plate club.  The element that added to the meal was the service.  We were there at the height of the lunch and rush and had a long 2 hour lunch. Our waiter was amazing. He kept things moving in his section as had the perfect balance of attentiveness without being a nuisance.  It was the perfect meal for a fun day with my sister

Charming restaurant, overlooking the indoor food market, Markthalle. My husband had the vitello tonato, which is one of his favorite dishes, he said this is one of the best he's had! Overall, the food and service were very good!

I don’t understand the bad reviews - we’ve been going to this restaurant (whenever we are in Stuttgart) for the past few years, and the food has always been consistently excellent.

Would recommend the grilled veal - it is very good. The service is also prompt and waiters friendly.
A very cozy place with a very special view on the stalls of the market below. Generally crowded but worth it. A bit pricy, though for what you get nur you pax for the stile italiano!
This place became our regular! And with the reason! See that tasty asparagus salad that I had ;)

editorial_summary.overview: Sushi, tempura & noodle soups, plus bento boxes, in an understated space with Japanese-style murals.

reviews.text: One of the best ramen I’ve had in Germany! You can taste it from the richness of the broth. I also just knew that the noodles are handmade, and it’s the perfect chewiness. The restaurant has the prefect ambience and quick service. My food came in around 10 minutes, which was very fast! Also applies to the other tables as well. I wil definitely try their bento next time!
Good choice of vegetarian food. We tried veg sushi and a noodle bowl. The taste was very good and the staff was very courteous and kind in serving us.

Service
Pretty fast and courteous. Was surprised the meal came out as fast as it did. Maybe 5 minutes after ordering it was brought to the table.

Food
I ordered the Beef Ramen and Parmeasran tuna sushi with a Tokyo Mule. The ramen was pretty good and the fried onions were very nice to a add a bit of crunch. A little spicy but nothing out of control. The only issue was it seemed like there should be more noodles/ramen in the dish. The sushi was creamy and paired very well with the ramen.  There was plenty of ginger, cucumber and mint in everything and I loved it.

Recommendation
One of the better Ramen places I have been to in awhile with delicious food and ridiculously fast service. If you are in the area it is definitely a must to stop by.

Really nice atmosphere in this Japanese restaurant. I really liked the fact that we had to take off our shoes to join the low table.
The sushis were really good.
Staff was friendly but they forgot our soups. We realized only when they brought us our sushis and we did not want to ask for it then. Well, except from that a good experience.

Meals, drinks and cocktails are very tasty and for me the perfect size!
The Service is friendly 😊
The ambiente is so comfortable and beautiful!
My favorite Japanese restaurant in Stuttgart ❤️

editorial_summary.overview: Classic Japanese noodle dishes & sushi platters in a bright, contemporary setting.

reviews.text: Excellent food. Tried Sushi and Katsu Ramen. The food was really delicious. Interior is enjoyable. Definitely recommend.
One of the rare places to do pretty decent udon soups. A varied menu and friendly service too.

Everything is delicious over here. Have been here several times and still it’s not enough. Definitely you should try sesame ice cream as i have not found something like this anywhere else. It’s really tasty (little bit sweet only)

I came to know Keyaki from a recommendation of a Japanese friend. He said that this is one of the most authentic sushi place in Stuttgart. Fast forward 5 years later, I frequently visit Keyaki, and it’s true what my friend said: they make the best sushi I’ve ever eaten!

The sushi are ok, nothing special: just an average quality and taste. No tap water even if you ask, only the bottles.

About interior - we have found that lighting level is not enough, also they can give you a table near the door even if you book in advance. I expected more than I got there.

editorial_summary.overview: Traditional Japanese sushi, sashimi, ramen & gyoza served in an unpretentious space.

reviews.text: We had Gyoza as a starter and Rahmen as main course.. The food was tasty but the service could be quicker

Absolutely amazed!
They restaurant is really cute and the personal so kind and helpful!

The food is delicious and I can't say anything for the price.

I have gluten allergy and as soon as I Informed the personal they made sure to give me many gluten free options.

I orded miso soup, which was perfect, not to sallty no to bland just perfect 👌

For my surprise the sushi rice also contains small amounts of gluten ( due the way that the prepare it) so the made sure to make my order with "normal rice" which doesn't contain gluten.

They even brought me gluten free soy sauce. Something that I really appreciate.

Unfortunately though the desserts aren't gluten free 😭 but I wouldn't be able to know this if the nice personal wouldn't have checked even the ice-cream ingredients.
Yes I was  "sad" for not being able to eat a dessert, but I was happy in the same time cause the really gave attention to my needs..

5 stars for me and I will definitely come back 👌

Amazing, authentic Japanese restaurant. Good sushi selection but it also resembles an izakaya style place. Staff is super friendly and very respectful. Food is amazing! I do recommend the sushi and Bärlauch-Gyoza. Also they have draft Kirin! I wanted to come again today, but they Are closed on Tuesdays.

Good variety of typical Japanese dishes besides sushi/sashimi. On the pricey side but worth the treat once in awhile. Loved the dessert concept of a sprouting pot plant (ice-cream with crumbly chocolate on top)

The place is so kawaii 😊 typical Japanese cute restaurant in Tokyo. We order obento, sakatari teller, okonomiyaki and zwei bonsai as a desserts. Everything is so good, definitely will come again. The obento reminds us of subway bento box in Tokyo.

editorial_summary.overview: Sushi, sashimi & grilled dishes in a compact dining space with traditional Japanese decor.

reviews.text: It’s an authentic Japanese food. So fresh, the taste not overpowering. It was just perfect. It made more special is they have tatami room. The service was also excellent! Will come again and try different menu.
A real Japanese restaurant, top quality. All people were from Japan. Real taste of Japan ! 🇯🇵

Outstanding place for Sushi & Japanese feel in Stuttgart! 😍
Feels & tastes authentic, fresh ingredients, wide choice, traditional interior, very kind & nice staff.
Absolute pleasure to visit!
My first ever  five star review in Stuttgart. Phenomenal presentation. Authentic sushi. Best flavors. Hands down superb. Fresh flavors and wide variety/assortment of fresh sushi.

Real Japanischen Restaurant! High quality of food and various variety of menu. And of course super friendly service. Highly recommended! Please try desserts as well especially if u are a Matha lover.. definitely worth it!!!

A small cosy place that offers you a sense of home and community. The food is great.   The positions are well curated and believe you me that two persons all mixed sushi is worth it and will make you full even without the starter or dessert. I had these with white wine and it was fresh from the bottle ( clearly a super good sign).

Advise, the seating is small so call in advance to RSVP. My friend and I didn’t and we waited for 10-15 mins ( very reasonable).

Also saw a lot of people coming in for takeaway so you are sorted either way.

This place is my best Sushi place in the whole of BW.

The most delicious japoneses entrees, soups, sushi and all its variations Böblingen has to offer. Friendly staff and the normal order waiting time knowing that you are getting the most fresh products as you can literally see your food getting ready in fort of you.
The room is small but very cozy and somehow you have all the space you need. I recommend you to do a reservation prior to your visit so you don’t have to wait for a table.
The bonus to all of this deliciousness is that you can enjoy it in the comfort of your own home. As you get the same fresh and delicious options delivered to you.
If you’re in doubt, don’t be! Go try it!

Absolutely delicious food fresh far from basic. Service is great and they put on a show for us which is really cool to see it highly recommend. Also really good for takeout because it is quite small so we also use take out there.

Fresh and very tasty sushi and miso soup. Staff is friendly and attentive. Cozy restaurant atmosphere. Price/quality is good compared to other sushi restaurants in town. I wish they were on some food app to order home delivery. I definitely recommend it.

I have been wanting to make a review! Ever since we moved to another country we miss tokoyo Sushi soo much! Not only everyone who works in there because they are so kind and attentive but also because the sushi is the best! If you haven’t you need to go to this place! I think about it everyday!

editorial_summary.overview: Classic Korean bibimbap & hot pot, plus stir-fries & rice rolls, in a compact, bright space.

reviews.text: Came here on Saturday evening around 1700. Waited for about 20 minutes. It was worth the wait. Staff was on point  the manager was very friendly and spoke English very well.  Food and drinks came out fast along with appetizers. The meal was hot and seasoned very well.. We will definitely come back here again.

I would say 4 since there was a slight mistake in the order. We mentioned ramen without any meat but it was made with meat. However, when we asked them the staff was very polite and apologized about the mistake and replaced it.

5/5 for service because the place doesn't accept card and we forgot to take cash with us, but they waited until we went and withdrew cash.

However, there was a huge waiting line when we visited so it is ideal to book in advance.

The same taste like in Korea🤍 I’ve been to many restaurants but not even half tastes like Korean dishes (because of international personal) Good portions, clean, everything were cooked really fast! the German women who took my order  don’t really know the menu but it’s good there’re working guys who helped 🫰🏻

It's authentic and tasty.  Worth money.
Every time I go to Stuttgart I go up here and have some Korean food..
This time was jajangmyeon with sea food..  yummy... The chop sticks are flat and little difficult to eat.  That's the only issue..
Menu with lot of variety, good service and excellent flavours

editorial_summary.overview: Dumplings, noodle bowls & Korean mains dished up in a relaxed restaurant with warm, wood decor.

reviews.text:
I ordered garlic and sweet chili flavor for myself, and I was wondering why it is not garlic at all. I told the waitress and he said it’s the wrong flavor. But they cannot do a new (half) portion, but offered me to use the rest of my plates (half of the half portion) and give it a second life as garlic flavor…

A portion costs 30 euro and it’s not even a whole chicken. What’s their problem???!!!!

Then I asked for a free drink for compensation, I ordered sparkling water, they gave me pure water….

I came here recently with my partner. We took a chance despite the rating being a 3.8 at the time. We got dumplings to share, bimbimbap and a seafood pancake. The dumplings didn't seem homemade. We were given the dumplings in their dish, my partner had chopsticks for their dish, and I had a fork and knife. We didn't get any small plates to eat the appetizer on (other tables appeared to receive plates). We had difficulty flagging down the waitstaff to get plates or another pair of chopsticks (it was very difficult to eat them with a fork without ripping the dumpling), we ended up with one person eating over the dish and the other eating over nothing and trying not to make a mess.

The banchan was surprising, the middle pickle element had three small pieces (see photo), we were very taken aback by the amount. It tasted ok.

The bimbimbap wasn't very flavorful but was ok enough to be edible. The seafood pancake (a dish that I have enjoyed at many other restaurants) felt doughy and was difficult to eat.

We were there on a very hot day and the restaurant was not well ventilated. We were a bit uncomfortable with the heat so partway through we asked to get the check and take the leftovers. I guess they only have those very small paper boxes (and maybe they were running out of the boxes?), because for each meal they packaged up less than half of what we had. The seafood pancake was just shoved into the box. We both had upset stomachs afterward.
It was sad to spend >50 eur on such a disappointing meal, but at least now we know to never come here again :/
Very kind and fast staff.  Food was delicious!!! Portions are great! Enough for midnight snack 😉
I was coming to Stuttgart for vacation and my friend recommends this restaurant. Staffs are kind, food taste good.

Good small restaurant but definitely not the best in germany in terms of fried chicken or anything else.

Food is fresh and tastewise also enjoyable.

Service was ok, not super friendly but also not rude or disinterested.

Two downsides:
- The food is definitely on the sweet side, the sauces as well as the side dishes
- price is quite high but you also get quite a hefty portion and unfortunately thats the only size they have. Especially the portion of their maindish which is the fried chicken (many different variations) is huge.

Overall definitely worth a try but I would recommend to go their with a group with at least 3-4+ person to enjoy all the different dishes. Otherwise you will try to finish one huge portion of the same dish.

editorial_summary.overview: Informal choice with low-key decor serving noodle soup, dumplings & other Korean comfort food.

reviews.text:
Friendly, fast and good.
When it comes to authentic Korean food, there's no way around Mandu in Stuttgart. It used to be a real insider spot, but today it's the place to be. The restaurant doesn't have an overloaded menu, they do what they know how to do and it's just awesome! I have been there several times over the years and have always enjoyed it.

Delicious food for reasonable prices. The bulgogi was amazing!!! The bibimbap wasn’t  as authentic because of the choice of vegetables but the flavour still satisfied me. Service was friendly and fast. Definitely recommended!

The food was excellent! Service was great and the price really reasonable. 11/10. We went there 2 days back to back because thats how good it was! Best Korean we had in Germany so far.
Can recommend the fried sweet-chilli chicken, the kimchi dumplings and kunmandu (vegetarian).
Super delicious! A total win, food-wise. Spicy!!

Hands down one of the best Korean restaurants in Stuttgart (although there really aren’t that many to begin with…). I’ve been here so many times already.

Their Galbi Mandu, the Korean beef dumplings, are super juicy and flavorful. Another excellent item to order is their Tteokbokki (Korean rice cakes in sweet spicy sauce) with Eomuk (fish cake/fischfrikadellen). The sweet and spicy Korean friend chicken is also a must when you come here.

The prices are extremely reasonable for a large quantity of food. I highly recommend!

June 19, 2023

Bulgogi Queen had not inspired me to write a story; alas, I fear that not every restaurant I want to write a review on will. After much turmoil, I decided that it's ok to write a review that differs from my usual style, and indeed if a place inspires storytelling then that is an accolade in of itself.

Starting with the appetizers, they were quite excellent. I thoroughly enjoyed the flavors of the kimchi. However, a friend remarked that it tasted store bought, I'm none the wiser. I would've also liked the portions of kimchi to be larger.

The long anticipated Korean fried chicken was a bit of a let down. While it received much praise from other members of our party, I found that a layer of the breading was soggy. It didn't have a nice crispiness that I expected, instead, it was a bit mushy. I'm guessing it's twice fried since it was just the inner layer that was unpleasant. Furthermore, the sauce was lacking, you can see in the picture that the sauce was not properly slathered on the chicken. It was poorly drizzled on and pooled at the bottom of the dish. The chicken itself was fairly decent, and I recall the sauce having good flavor.

The items of the main course were a hit or miss. The smattering of meats had some success when they were marinated. However, half the meats were outright plain, not marinated or seasoned at all. And let's be real, the bit of salt and sauce they provide on the side isn't the proper way to prepare meat for a grill. It was disappointing that this was the premium menu set, and for the price I wouldn't recommend it. If you follow my reviews then you'll know I'm not afraid to pay for good food. Lastly, the morsels that were marinated proved to be quite tasty.

My final rating is, "There's room for easy improvement. I do not plan on returning, except perhaps for specific menu items."

Bulgogi Queen is a Korean restaurant located in Stuttgart, Germany, that specializes in serving authentic Korean cuisine. Customers have praised Bulgogi Queen for its high-quality ingredients and flavorful dishes, including their Bulgogi.

Reason for 3 Stars:
Some of the dishes are a bit salty and lacking of some traditional taste. This can be due to adjusting flavours based on country.
If they offer the traditional taste, it will be a big jump.

The Fried chicken though on the other hand is a bomb!! A must try.

In addition to Bulgogi, Bulgogi Queen offers a wide range of other Korean dishes, such as Bibimbap, Japchae, and Korean Fried Chicken. The restaurant has a cozy and welcoming atmosphere, and the staff is friendly and accommodating.

Overall, if you're in Stuttgart and looking for Korean bbq, it‘s for you. 😊

Visited in January 2023

Kimchi soup sadly didn’t have much taste.
The fried Kimbap and the Veggie Pancake were drenched (!!!) in oil and so soggy, we couldn’t eat them (I understand that fried foods can be oily but we expected the coating to be crispy and not squishy and oily, it tasted fairly disgusting).
The service was friendly at first but when they asked us about the food we answered honestly (that it was way too oily) and they only looked at us in disbelief. It was pricy conpared to what we got.

Maybe it’s better when you order the BBQ sets (the table next to us had a BBQ set and it looked tasty).

Walked in at 17:30 and the place was very busy. Was given a table only until 19:00 hrs... understandable. Ordered the BBQ for 2. Beautiful presentation and food was fresh. Lots of meat and lettuce but side dishes like the kimchee was very little. Rice bowl was about 2 big spoons full. Learned that if you want more rice is extra, never heard of that before. Enough meats for 2 people and tasty meat. The waitresses seemed stressed and rushed. Busy place and packed. Needs better circulation, you definitely leave there smelling like grill. Didn't like that they were grabbing everything out of the table even before we finish eating reaching across us without asking. Now to the end...when we paid the bill was about 82 Euros. Gave her 90 Euros and she started walking out without giving or asking if we want the change. Usually we will tip well but because of her assumption we stopped her and asked for the change. She didn't like it and made a mad face. And she was not the one that even served us through the whole process! Not cool at all. Overall the food was fresh, good but not sure if we will return.
We loved the Korean BBQ (Gui)! Food was tasty and the staff were quick to repond with bringing us more when we were running low. Truly amazing dining experience here!

Small place BUT taste is awesome.
Recommended for Korean food in Germany

We had the bibimbab, bulgolgi and shared the mandu dumplings. Everything was delicious and tastes like it is homemade. The owner was so sweet and makes everyone who walks in the door feel really welcome. We saw a groups of regulars come in and she greeted them like family. Overall a warm experience for a very cold and rainy day.

Oh! Don't forget to ask for kimchi! I'm not usually big on it- but I could not stop eating it.

Ps. Bring cash

Headen Bibimbap is a cosy restaurant which has a nice layout and a great cook. It is an uncomplicated menu with 14 dishes and a lot of Korean refreshing drinks on offer. Very reasonably priced and quick service. You can enjoy most of their dishes guilt free as the food feels comfortable. The quantity is also great for the price

Nice place, lovely owner and indeed Korean good food, do not expect the same as from top notch Korean restaurants bt the given the price you can eat healthy and to your fullest satisfaction. It is not the coziest places, rather to grab a quick bite.

An authentic Korean taste!
It’s a small kitchen and no fuss, but really great place to get a quick, home cooked meal. Highly recommended.

I went there a few days ago with my husband and our little daughter and we loved it so much if I could give more stars, I would definitely do it! Very friendly staff and delicious food!  Highly recommended!

Food was really good, we tried all the appetizers and the gyoza and the kimchi fritters were super, as main we took bibimbap and I also liked a lot. Service was fast and really friendly. The only think i would improve is the menu, is really reduced and in one visit you tried almost everything. This makes you think again if you want to come back and try something different.
The food is good , so much flavours but it is also not cheap and the restaurant is not very fancy dining, but very suitable for a nice dinner. I would certainly come back.

What a great modern take on Korean food. The dishes are simple but the flavors definitely authentic Korean. Very clean restaurant and we have always received friendly service, they are English friendly and accept credit cards.

ALL menus were amazing!!! Taste reminded me of moms recipe back home in very fascinating colorful dish- especially bibimbab! Definitely will go back to try other dishes and loved the kind Korean lady- super nice😎
Very goooood ❤️
Average , not that great ice cream

so delicious 😋
Two balls ➕ biscuits are only 3.6 Euros and NT$120! ❤️❤️
Fresh ice cream, medium selection, cheap.

editorial_summary.overview: Bright, informal Argentinian cafe with outside seating & occasional live tango shows.

reviews.text: Small, cafe style place but we've just had the best steaks ever. Served simply with a choice of chips or potatoes and salads. Steaks (rump and ribeye) were so tender and well flavoured. Seek this place out if you find yourself in Stuttgart.

Came here on Sunday with the family. It's a small resturant but very clean and friendly. The staff was very friendly. Victor served us and is a great guy.  The food was excellent. I must rate them with a great review. This steak house is great with their portions than Abbaccos steak house and better quality than Block house. Victor, thank yiu for that shot of Tequila too..
This is the best meat I have ever had in my life and the service amazing just like the food. You get what you pay for.

It’s rare to have such a great eating experience in Stuttgart. The restaurant looks very normal from the outside. However, the owner and the team make you feel more than home. Awesome service and recommendations from everyone with a big smile on their face. The steaks are incredible and very fairly priced. The sides are really good. The condiments are amazing. I can’t recommend this restaurant enough.
The meat was outstanding, both in flavour and cooking point. For sure one of the best in the area. The staff is nice, polite and always willing to help. Will return again for sure.

Amazing food, but service was pretty poor.
We got the daily menu and the rice porkbelly dish. Was really delicious and worth the money. However we went there yesterday and waited 40 mins for our drinks only. Got the food after 1½ hours. After we finished I asked for the dessert we ordered when we got there. The waitress told us it was sold out, which was weird because we paid for it at the beginning. Also our clothes smelled pretty bad after we left the restaurant and still holds on. The restaurant should have managed people waiting outside for their table to get ready. With all the people waiting in the middle of the restaurant it caused a big crowd, made it pretty hard to go to the toilet or waitresses going through. Also a women (not on purpose) got the back of her jacket in my food which was pretty sad and a bit nasty. I would go again, if the service improves
The vibe was amazing, we ordered ceviche (delicious) and seco (lamb was tender but the pork was super dry). Sadly we couldn’t try the dessert tres leches because we had to leave the table …

Tap water!!!
Whatever we ordered was very tasty and very well made. The stuff was friendly and accommodating. The music was a bit too loud for a relaxing meal. The ordering is a bit cantina style (order and pay on the counter) and the bookings have fixed duration, but those shortcomings are annulled by the fact that this place has the common decency of offering TAP WATER! Respect!
Wow! Extremely delicious! Flavourful  dishes and spectacular service. I’ll  gladly visit you often. South America well represented. Thanks a lot!!!!

This restaurant is like returning to Ecuador for lunch. Food is fresh and delicious if you are in the mood for seafood this is the place to be!! Servers are very friendly and the atmosphere is perfect to enjoy a couple of beers

Been to this place couple of times.
Food quantity & taste is good.
Recommend to make appointments if you are going on weekends.

We tried just Margaritas with a group of friends after work. It was Happy Hour 🍻 until 22:30 and the prices were so good 😊, we paid 6,6€ for Margarita Classic. The service was good, he did nice recommendations.

The drinks were excellent considering the prices during happy hours. At full price I would probably not prefer the same. The fajitas and  tacos were tasty enough but I'd strictly stay away from the burritos and the bowls. In the end I would go back considering the high costs for relatively average food.

Our group have had many events here. Gets very very crowded and sometimes takes a while to get drinks but that's a sign of how popular it is! We got a reservation just before the end of Happy hour at 8pm. All cocktails are half price until 8pm and then again after 11:30pm. Our tip, try the touch down cocktail!

Great atmosphere and service,  verg nice stuff.
Food amazing tastes amazing , i treied chicken  fajeta and steak fajeta.
It was with great dips and sides .
Also they make the best coconut kiss drink.
Also very nice vergin mojeto.
I really recommend to try it.

I have been living in Stuttgart for the last five months as an exchange student, and I have tried almost every single Mexican restaurant this city has to offer. I’m used to a good deal of Texmex or authentic Mexican food, and Joe Peñas was what I was looking for. Me and my friends went to celebrate my twenty first birthday so we went all out for the food. We all got drinks at the restaurant, the Joes Margarita is fantastic and I heavily recommend it to anyone that stops by, we also shared the chips and dip. While the cheddar cheese dip was only okay, every other dip was fantastic. It was a Tuesday so I ordered from the taco menu and got the LA tacos, they were so good I couldn’t even stop to take a picture of them before I started eating. The atmosphere at the restaurant was fantastic and the staff was always there when we needed them.
Exceedingly bigger portions than anticipated, not super cosy atmosphere perhaps because the tables are way too close to each other. Friendly staff & fast service. Would definitely recommend

Excellent food. Really enjoyed my Enchiladas de Pollo. Big portions! Would surely return, despite extremely slow service (hence 4 stars), which was probably because of the staff shortage on the evening of my visit as per the waiter.
Delicious food! Tacos on Taco Tuesday are my favorites! Burrito is also really nice! Cocktails are not that good.

Just want to have a late snack. They let us in even tough we didn’t make any reservation.
The service was good and friendly. Food was awesome, especially the guacamole its so fresh and tasty and it also family friendly.

We have been four times since arriving from Italy. Every dish has been excellent. We especially enjoy the stuffed avocado and the chili con carne, washed down with margaritas and Dunkel Weißen. On Sunday from noon to 1500, we had “All You Can Eat” spare ribs that were amazing — the meat was tender and fell off the bones! Perfect! Olga is a GREAT Cook and Marcel is an excellent bartender. Amazingly for me they also can make many dishes Vegan and already offer Vegetarian dishes. The Vegan ice cream is delicious.
Truly a gem balancing a need for Mexican food in Germany and still able to cater to the German customers. Not an easy task

Cute, off the path Tex-Mex place. It's sort of hard to find. This is not a stereotypical "Mexican" restaurant like in the states, though. The nachos were chips with shredded cheese placed in the oven to melt it. The meat was quite greasy. Still, it was pretry good.

The staff was nice but it took a while to get food. It appeared that they were a little understaffed. The food was good. I wouldn't compare it to Mexican food in the States or Mexico because there was a different spin on the ingredients but it was tasty. It's also pretty unique to watch people riding horses in the paddock while eating.

We have been here a couple of times. I like the ambience...relaxing and reflects Mexico culture...food was great. My son and wife liked the quesadillas. The outside seating during the summer is relaxing and a must do. I would recommend to people who have kids... go there with kids to show around the horse farm. We like the service there...Freddy who helped us and served us better.

First thing you would think there’s Mexican food but that’s not the case. It’s a decent restaurant for Germany but not for anyone who’s used to Mexican food. Quesadilla was the best thing they’ve offered. Guacamole is prepared using a blender! You’ll notice the smooth watery texture. You’re looking for tacos, it’s served only on Tuesdays! Atmosphere is nice in the restaurant and you’ll enjoy watching the sweet old pug limping around.

Simply speaking, this is the BEST take on Mexican food in the country. Fresh ingredients and made from scratch. The owener and waitstaff fully engages with the customs to make an enjoyable experience. I remember their food and friendly staff from years before at their other location and their friendly welcoming smiles were as if i had never left. Absolutely the highest recommendation i can offer. Keep doing what you are doing and see you next time.

I know, I shall first give the comment about the food but I was so impressed about their Signature Caipirinha Tequila Cocktail. It was very good, love it! The food were also very tasty and the service was very, very nice.
Very delicious and authentic food, awesome and very friendly staff. One suggestion, call exactly at 5PM if you want to go on weekends else you will not get table!

Important to note: There are some very negative comments on here that represent spoiled Americans. Please do you best to ignore these comments.

This restaurant is one of the best in the Stuttgart area. Been twice, had the enchilada burrito the first time and the tacos the second. Both fantastic and hit all the right spots. I especially enjoy their chipotle salsa, and the drinks are to die for (Marg on the rocks!). I also have no idea what some of the reviews on here are talking about, the staff (Both waitress & chef) were super friendly and helpful. 10/10 recommend.

The pictures/video feature the nachos, which our table shared.

Instantly put this place on my fav food list. The nachos, the salsas, the Mojito, the interior, the service and the details and of course the food are an authentic homage to the Mexican cuisine. I got the veggie burrito medium spicy it was worth every single bite! 🌯🌮🌶️

editorial_summary.overview: Burrito & bowl variations, plus an array of salads, at a bright, shabby-chic place with a terrace.

reviews.text:
Ingredients didn’t taste fresh at all and chicken was nothing like chicken. The guy who rolled our burritos, did a pretty bad job and same ingredients were kept together, either eating only rice, beans or chicken.

Only star for a good hygiene.

Overall, disappointed!

Direct copy of the American Chipotle restaurant with the same meat options, but fewer salsas.  The meats need more flavor, but this is about as close to Mexican as you will find in Stuttgart so it's a good option.

6/4/23
I like to start my reviews on a positive note before getting into the critical parts. So the food was enjoyable enough, it certainly wasn't bad by any means.

When biting into a burrito the feeling you're supposed to have is "omg, what the **** is this amazingness." That was not experienced here.

The spicy pork burrito was nothing to write home about - home for me being San Diego. I don't think the pork itself was spicy, I think they named it spicy pork cause of the sauce they used which was not spicy by any reasonable definition of the word. But I suppose we are in Germany and I've grown accustomed to not expect much of Mexican inspired cuisine here (Burritos are actually an American invention). Especially where spice is concerned. Don't get me wrong, I'm not one of these spicy freaks who enjoy the pain, just good flavor. Even purely from a flavor perspective, the salsa was a let down. The brown rice was a bit bland as well, they had a lime seasoned rice that looked decent though. To name a few things I did enjoy, the tortilla, beans, and corn which gave a nice sweetness and change of texture.

I'm willing to go back to try the beef burrito, but as it stands my rating is: "I'd rather continue suffering from deprivation of Mexican food than eat here... But I suppose for those who don't know better, the place isn't all that bad and if my friends want to go then I wouldn't complain."

Taste was good and the price was also appropriate :) they also had nice music playing. However there are a few points that could easily be improved and change th experience for the better:

1) the Burrito was cold (still tasty). They should definitely warm the burrito up in a grill after assembling it!
2) The bathroom needs to be cleaned! It’s very dirty which is a shame.
3) The display in which the ingredients are kept made them look a bit less attractive.

Nevertheless a nice place I would come again.

The prices were ok and the team was friendly!
Big Plus: real Valentinea!!

reviews.text: Waiters were incredibly nice and attentive, the best i’ve met in Stuttgart. Everything was really clean and the food is delicious. The pizza with purple potato is AMAZING, i want to go back just to order it again. Make a reservation a day or two in advance because it is always full, even on weekdays.
Recommended place for big gatherings with group of people. Cozy interior, various pizza, comparably fast serving, and the pizza was delicious!

The strong points are: the price and the speed with which the pizzas are made. I am definitely not used to German/Stuttgart market but for Northern Italian one very much: in my vision the choice of pizzas is too much simplified. Would suggest to add at least yet 4 tastes. The service is attentive and quick.
Best pizza not only in Stuttgart, but in the entire Germany! Service and food was excellent. The place is beautiful   They speak English and accept cards.

Tasty pizza dough, the ingredients were also decent (Italian tomatoes, buffalo mozzarella, etc.). However the pizza size really depends on the mood of the chef. Out of three pizzas, one was a regular 30cm pizza while the other two where 20 to 25cm. Keep in mind that I ordered all three same pizzas. So, all in all it is an authentic Italian restaurant governed by Italians, while the food size and quality can vary based on the mood of the chef.

We were very disappointed. Mushroom pizza was very dry, cold and the mozzarella tomato pizza with rocula was even drier. In the end, tomatoes and mozzarella just lay on top like a salad plate and kept the pizza cold. Worst pizza ever, even cutting the pizza was very bad. 🤬🤮

Hands down my favorite pizza place in the area. Their pizzas and pastas are delicious!! We have tried several different kinds and have enjoyed them all!! The pizza crust is the perfect texture, and they put the right amount of ingredients on the pizza. My family orders from here at least once a week, and it’s become one of our favorites!!
Not only fresh and delicious pizza 🍕 and pasta 🍝, Da Luigi has the best Tiramisu dessert 🍨 in town 👍👍highly recommended! 🇮🇹
Finally luigi has his own Pizzeria,
Good Food
Our favorite Italian in Stuttgart east! Pasta, pizza, arrancini always delicious and for reasonable prices. The owners are always frindly and welcoming.

Update to my initial 2-star rating...

After a couple of flawless deliveries I can say that the pizza is still good and mistakes can happen sometimes.
If you’re in the area, I’d recommend stopping by.

*********

Usually great pizza, it’s our favorite in Ost so far. Just today it left mixed feelings.
Chose a pizza without cheese from the menu and added an extra note with ‚no cheese on the pizza please‘... guess what arrived.
This is my favorite Pizzeria in Stuttgart-Ost. They have the best price-quality ratio, mainly do take-away but there are also 4 or 5 tables on site. Owner and staff are very friendly and effective

Nobody from the service came to me for 15 minutes so I had to go inside and make the order myself. After that I waited 1 hour for my pizza and people who came later than me had their pizzas first... And the pizza is not like in Italy, it wasn't thin
The best pizza in town. Fast and reliable delivery. Great and friendly service. Original Italian taste. I highly reccomend arancino and pizza mafiosa.

An absolute jewel for pizza lovers!! For us, one of the best pizza in town (around Stuttgart also). We live in the city and come here for pizza very often. The staff is very nice, last time it took quite a bit longer than normally cause it was pretty full, but we still waited for it :) They also have a delicious Bio-Beer that we wish we could buy to have at home. Can only recommend!

Local pizza restaurant with Napolitano pizza style, unexpectedly very tasty!  The interior is not so nice, location also, but if you are looking for good pizza in Stuttgart, one of the best I have tried in Baden-Wurttemberg!
Delicious pizza from the oven, highly recommend this place

Have been visiting this restaurant on a Friday around noon as I was nearby and it was top rated ( average of 4.6 with 571 reviews ). They serve starters, salads, pizza, panuzzo and deserts.

Due to the high average rating and the amounts of reviews I have had pretty high expectations. Food was very delicious and fairly priced.

Staff was very friendly - people in the kitchen, which can be viewed from the restaurant - were also speaking italian so expect typical Pizza.
One of the most amazing pizza's I've ever had. Tiramisu was great too

Great pizza. If you know anything about cooking, you realize right away how much work and passion went into the dough and the selection of ingredients. The owner is so passionate and humble. The service is friendly and accommodating. The price is high, but you pay for the high quality and the journey the chef wants to take you on.

The 5 stars are for the pizza itself. The pizza was delicious, the high quality of the ingredients and workmanship made for a taste experience to be remembered. Kudos to the owner, chef and the staff.
Getting this important part out of the way, let's focus also on other small details to be considered, helpful to manage expectations.
The pizzeria is not located in a downtown area, instead it's in a nice neighborhood with street parking. Which may be full, depending on the time you get there. Have patience to find a parking spot.
It's a small restaurant, similar to small Italian pizzerias', but not a fancy place. Typical square small tables, super useful to create the space needed by the number of expected guests.
The staff was friendly, helpful and catering to your needs all through the course of the meal.
The menu contains a good variety of pizza types, trying to highlight the ingredients and their provenance; with also wine choices for each pizza. But beware not, they also have beer. ;)
I'd recommend a redesign of the menu in a more professional way, as it's quite a headache to read and understand. The layout of the information can be way more efficient.
One improvement I hope they make before my next visit is an upgrade on the coffee. The espresso coffee quality was subpar, tasted very sour, totally not matching the Italian espresso taste.
Price wise, it's on the higher end, at least from my perspective. I can accept it considering it's in a big city like Stuttgart and the pizza was really a delight for all my taste buds.
Well worth making the effort to drive to it.

Absolutely brilliant! Deserves 5+ Stars. Authentic Italian Beer, cocktail menu, incredible pizzas with reasonable price for the size. You will not go hungry here. staff very friendly. We'd love to come back!

My family and I ate here for a our New Year's lunch (on 02 Jan) and it was fabulous!  From start to finish; the food, the drinks, service, and ambiance.  Freshest seafood we have enjoyed to date in Europe and everything was incredible.  The tuna tataki and the smoked salmon sampler platter were first rate and the raw oysters on hand were as if just out of the ocean. reviews.text:
One of the best All You Can Eat restaurant I’ve eaten in - so worth my money! We came in for lunch (17.90€ per person without drinks) with my friend who is a frequent customer there (it’s my first time eating here since I recently moved to Stuttgart). The restaurant is huge and clean, with nice relaxing ambience. Service is top notch and very kid-friendly, which could be a plus point for some.

Now for the food:
So unlike other AYCE restaurant that is like running sushi, this one you can order via tablet. A nice touch! I recommend going out with friends so you can try many of their varieties and enjoy time together.

They serve salad, appetizers, rolled sushi, maki, nigiri, grilled (like yakitori), fried stuff. The sushi is not that special, but surprisingly I like the grilled and fried items (recommend the tempura, yakitori, and cheese stick). Each menu has a descrption in German and English, so you can choose based on dietary restrictions.

You may say there are lots better sushi or grill places (of course they are!) - but remember this is all you can eat so I compare it with similar restaurants that also offer the same systems. Unlike the usual greasy fried stuff served at other places, it was none like that. The salmon and other fish were also quite fresh, and that is important for a sushi place.

Lastly, there is also desert (you have to take on your own). There are cakes, donuts, melon, watermelon, and huge selection of ice cream - I was quite surprised (cos usually in AYCE there are only 3-4 flavors)! Tried 3 scoops (I’m a huge fan of ice cream 🍦): black bean, green tea, and another pink colored. They were all nice, not like the cheap ones (you can really taste the difference).

So all in all, my experience is really worth the money I spent here (note: we went on Wednesday afternoon, so the restaurant is not that busy). I would actually bring my friends if they’re visiting Stuttgart one day, and so should you! 👍🏻

When you look at the food counter, not just the soup, you can have an incredible appetite even if you are full.
Personally, as someone who has been a Restaurant Management for 20 years, I say it's amazing.
Bless your hands, your heart, your work 👍
👏👏👏👏👏👏
Raw meat, food came 50 minutes after ordering. Table was dirty. I didn't order a salad but got it and had to pay for it!

reviews.text: Tasty kebab with high quality hand made and home made bread, yufka, Pizza etc..I love to eat here because of friendly service and tasty food. I recommend to try it here and enjoy your experience with wonderful and good Quality food.
Thin pizza. Tastes especially good with the spicy powder they have.

Pizza and Tee gut, Lahmacun Spezial durchschnittlich. Portionen zu dies Preis klein. Ich habe gegessen, werde es aber nicht wiederholen.

Pizza and tea good, lahmacun special average. Small portion for this price. I ate it, but you know I won't do it again.
We were with a larger group at Ayaz, we had a lot of fun with the owners, who were extremely hospitable! Very inconspicuous, but really great kebab shop! We'd love to come by again.

Unfortunately the quality has decreased a lot. The bread was doughy and bland and the kebab itself was lightly topped. Unfortunately, value for money is bad. Wouldn't come again. It's a shame, it was really better!
We ordered home delivery and the food came super fast, probably in maximum 15 minutes. Thanks!
the first time come the food was wonderful and service very nice
Excellent prices, quality, quantity and menu selections! I was stuffed for $6 Euro. Little warm in the restaurant but not unbearable.

We went to there shop ordered chicken doner and requested them kindly cut fresh from the grill the guy refused to give us the fresh one hot and rather gave us cold old cut which was not at all juicy and hot. I waisted my money. More over the bread was really hard and unfriendly server.
I won’t  recommend this Kabab shop. Nor I will visit again.

By the time this place changed ownership, it went from the worst in town to one of the best in the city. Clean, very friendly and the quality and taste is really good. Especially the pizza is one of the best I have ever tasted. 5/5 clearly, recommend to taste and you gonna fall in love.

editorial_summary.overview: Simple Vietnamese cafe & take-out joint known for pho noodles, spring rolls & vegetarian options.

reviews.text:
I recommend this restaurant if you want to try vietnamese food. To ask your food you have to go to the vitrine and then you get a number. After that they serve the food at your table. The food is really good and fast preparation.
The atmosphere it's okay, the restaurant is simple and a bit small, they could improve playing some ambient music to and more decorative space.

Food: quite good, nothing special but still enjoyable and for the amount of food you get, it‘s actually pretty cheap

Ambience: a bit tight and old dated decoration, but still ok and staff ist also friendly

Maybe for somebody who is new: you have to order your dishes straight at the checkout and also grab ur own cutlery, the service only brings the food to ur table.

I‘m not sure if I like this concept, but it‘s definitely faster in general. Maybe u can compare it to the chain „Vapiano“

This is a great place to get some authentic Vietnamese flavors that one normally cannot find at other German-Vietnamese restaurants.

I always get number 25, the Beef Com Thit, and it’s delicious! The lemongrass marinade on the beef is delectable, and the homemade fish sauce they serve with it has a great balance between umami flavors and notes of citrus.

For the price, you can’t go wrong here!

Don’t know if it’s because I was hungry but I think this might be the best pho I’ve had in Germany so far. And that’s comparing it to 6 other places in other German cities. I will definitely be back😁. Forgot to take a picture because I was hungry🙈

Cosy place and you also get delicious Vietnamese food, what else one needs during winter? Amazing Thai curry with well cooked rice. Vegetarian rolls were crispy enough with decent amount of filling. Must try if you are into south Asian food. This place offers quite affordable and tasty food.

Authentic homemade Vietnamese Food.
Everything is really tasty. The variety of the menu is so great.
I love the Bun Nem with noodles, springs rolls, fresh salad and dressing.
The soups are also great.
Nice staff 👍

Despite the fact that it took 2hrs till our food delivered, the taste was very mediocre. Most of the other vietnamese restaurants in Stuttgart taste better than what we ordered yesterday (Ca ri do, pho xao - quite basic vietnamese dish not even difficult to cook). Def. Not recommend for people who knows asian cruisine :/

Been looking for an authentic bowl of pho in the city. As a Vietnamese, I could tell the broth was cooked with love and patience. The flavours were deep and very well balanced. This reminded me of my home town in Vietnam. I will come back again for sure :))

Good quick food. Generally helpful staff.

Worth a visit when you're shopping in the area and in the mood for Vietnamese food.
Amazing and very delicious food! Great quality at very reasonable price! Had Bun Nem and was like in Vietnam!

Ambience is really beautiful and staff is very nice so the service. But, food is just normal. Over-priced restaurant. No taste in food. If you’re a fan of interior, try it. Otherwise just waste of money. Seriously, too pricy restaurant. Ordered a meal, half of the portion is just filled with leaves.

Fresh and tasty Vietnamese food. A little expensive and fairly small portions for German standards but if you don’t mind that, your taste buds will say thank you. For what I had on the pictures (homemade lemonade included) I paid 30 euros. It was really all delicious, quality has a price.
Not to mention the pleasant setting and the friendly service.

Had a very good dinner here. Was craving for some good Asian food and Vietal did not disappoint. Mekong Surf & Turf and Dragonsea (taste like Tomyam soup). Hearty and satisfying meal for 2. Highly recommended 👍
The restaurant looks really attractive from the outside, which makes me walk in spontaneously. Charming decorations and atmosphere. Food is good.

Over-hyped Asian fusion without taste. We asked for soy to get something out of it, but it was sweet. The volcano sault and lime brought by the service, helped in the end. If the food flavor improved, it would be great and I would come back. We love to have a good place to go out in East. PS. Please remove the lettuce from the dishes. Thx

editorial_summary.overview: Cosy Vietnamese restaurant plating traditional dishes, from pho soup to noodles.

reviews.text: Delicious Vietnamese food! Friendly staff and cozy atmosphere! but food takes some time compare to other restaurants..
Tasty fresh food, friendly staff, quick service, clean restaurant. Can’t complain!
Cozy Restaurant, nice atmosphere. Great traditional Hanoi-style vietnamese food and friendly service. I would come again!

The space is really nice, and the price is quite high
The summer roll is good, but I don’t like the Lach with vegetables

It was an evening where we wanted to try some new restaurant. Looking for Vietnamese restaurants we found Send Viet and decided to try. The place is cosy, the right amount of tables and a relaxed atmosphere. We ordered a dish of Vorspeisen for 2 and 2 mains. The service was friendly and fast, I really appreciated the explanations before eating and the suggestions on the sauces. The antipasti were just great, tasty, full of flavors, different. The mains were just great: fresh vegetables, an rainbow of flavors exploding in your mouth. The ratio quality/price absolutely good.
Overall I liked everything, only one thing I would change: the color of the chair 😀
