reviews.text: I was expecting way more from this place. We ordered pick up at least 40 minutes before, and when we arrived, we were told we had to wait longer. After waiting another 35 minutes the food finally came out. We were told nothing about why the food was taking so long. We also got no offer of water or drinks or anything for the wait. We ordered some super basic meals. Two fresh summer rolls, and a noodle beef bowl. Nothing special. Replace taken me less time to go to the store and cook it. Prices are high, and the service is lacking.  The food itself isn’t bad. Just not worth the wait.

Delicious food!
Deserve 5 stars ..
I have been to many restaurants this one is the best so far. very polite and humble staff if you are looking for good food with good vibes you must visit I will definitely recommend to everyone .

Recommended by a Vietnamese colleague, we had to go to the place.
The gastronomic adventure starts when you open the door as the place smells like heaven (food heaven I mean). The food was excellent with plenty of choice to make everyone happy. We ordered a started plate for 4 which was amazing as we could try basically all starters offered by the card.
The tables are not too close to each other like in most restaurants in Germany and it feels good.
Dogs are allowed.
The only bad point was the price of the drinks. We ended up paying pretty much and realized it was not because of the food. Nevertheless I would totally recommend the place
Food is delicious and authentic (especially Tom Kha), atmosphere and service are  really nice and friendly. Definitely will try to visit this place again!

Service: quite busy so expect long waits

Setting: clean, spacious

Food: I had fried veg with tofu, it was ok, but I've certainly had better. A little dry

Price:  about overpriced. For a lemonade, fried veg and tofu, and mini spring rolls 23 EUR.  I think 18 EUR would be a more fair price

editorial_summary.overview: Laid-back Vietnamese restaurant for familiar eats like spring rolls, pho, chicken katsu & noodles.

reviews.text:
I recently visited Viet Wok restaurant and had an amazing experience! The food was absolutely delicious, especially dish number 72 with fried duck and chicken with rice. The flavors were perfectly balanced and left me wanting more. The service was super quick and friendly, which made the dining experience even more enjoyable.

I also tried the Vietnamese coffee and it was incredible! The strong flavor was just what I needed to perk up my day. The atmosphere of the restaurant was very clean and comfortable, making it the perfect place to enjoy a meal with friends and family.

Overall, I highly recommend Viet Wok restaurant to anyone who loves authentic Vietnamese cuisine. The dishes are flavorful, the service is top-notch, and the coffee is a must-try! Don't miss out on this gem of a restaurant.

Authentic Vietnamese restaurant in the heart of Hallein ☺️🤍

Highly recommended for those who want to try authentic Vietnamese food in Salzburg. This place is excellent in every way, from its warm and friendly customer service, and great Vietnamese food to a wonderful view from its patio.

Absolutely amazing food. Small cozy restaurant. Had duck in peanut sauce and rice, delicious. Must try.

Update: still amazing, the best Vietnamese food in Stuttgart.

Go there!!

I love love love the restaurant. The food was good and big portions. They also let me customize my order.

I highly recommend the vietnamese iced coffe. It's to die for 🥰🥰

Friendly owners

Only downside it that it closed at 21h30 but still so friendly and let us stay to finish our drinks.

Oh and we were both offered chopsticks :)

Decent vietnamese place for lunch. Quick service and friendly.

Pho and Meat dishes looked plain but decently flavored.

Not a bad place to visit if you are near and needing lunch.

editorial_summary.overview: Various Asian dishes turned out in a snug, modern space with outdoor tables & a take-out option.

reviews.text: Nice place & really good taste
Is a small restaurant but the food and the attention that you get is amazing. The portion size is generous and the prices are great.
Been here several times. Love the noodle variety here. The price is OK and the place is nice. In summer we can also sit outside.
cosy family run restaurant, quick, delicious and cooked with much love for their happy customers. place for delicious  asian food....beautiful people..
Delicious asian food

editorial_summary.overview: Vietnamese spring rolls, pho soups, salads & spicy curries at a bright contemporary venue.

reviews.text:
We had a great lunch here! Fantastic food, cozy ambient upstairs (although it looks like a fast food restaurant at the entrance downstairs) and friendly service.

I don't have any idea about authentic vietnamese food but for me the restaurant made a very good impression. The food was tasteful, especially the baked duck was one of the best we had so far. Can recommend :)

They just accepted Cash when we have been there in the beginning of January 2023.

UPDATE:  Still the best Pho place in downtown Stuttgart.  Good flavor, good portion, and quick service.
Extra star on the atmosphere because the second floor is better decorated.

Fantastic Pho. The best Pho restaurant in Stuttgart. Good price good portion excellent broth.
Great in winter.

Food was good - although English translation on their menu was rubbish - ordered the crab soup, came as prawns soup, ordered ravioli, came triangle veggie spring rolls, & the beef was too chewy - good service & friendly staff however the translation was scheisser
A nice little gem I’ve found!  Will be back!  Ordered the große Phô Bo (F6).  Served with a generous amount of both noodle and beef.  Deeeelish!  It is a cash only place for now.

We were at the city and want something quick to eat. The papaya salad and beef noodle taste good, however, the beef a little bit tough. They should cook it longer or using sukiyaki meat so its thiner and more fat. Overall it was ok

I come here everytime I'm in Stuttgart, The food is very good and exactly what you want when you eat Vietnamese.
The atmosphere is a bit rustic and reminds me more of a traditional austrian restaurant or a ski hut. The staff is friendly and fast.
Recommend!

What a nice little gem tucked away in Stuttgart! As soon as I walked in and smelled the citrusy fish sauce, I knew that this place would be authentic. We had the Beef Pho (northern Vietnamese style) and Chicken Bun. Both were quite good. We will be back again 😁
Delicious food and friendly stuff
When the weather is warm, one could dine Al fresco. Otherwise the inside looked like a German pub. It’s our go-to place for Pho Bo, Banh Xeo (pancakes stuffed with prawns and pork), and nems.

I ordered the Pho Ga there, the broth is really good, rich in flavor and very fresh as well. Not salty at all. Also the chicken slices are super tender and delicious, I drunk all the soup in the pho. Unbelievable. Family restaurant vibes, love it. Recommended!

editorial_summary.overview: Chic, cozy restaurant offering familiar Vietnamese appetizers, main dishes & soups, plus cocktails.

reviews.text: Came for early dinner yesterday. Great food and atmosphere. Reasonably priced food and wait staff friendly. The beef Pho could have been seasoned more with beef broth. The food overall was very good.

Wanted to try this restaurant as it's one of the better Vietnamese restaurants in the area (on Google).

Service
Came a little after they opened up but very respectful, polite, and quickly got us seated. Attentive and even though the food did take a bit long to come out it was hot and fresh.

Food
Good the sampler platter as an appetizer and Bo Lac Luc. My company ordered the Beef Pho. The appetizer was good, but couldn't tell much difference between the fried spring roll or the pork roll but it was hot. The Bo Lac Luc was amazing great flavor and hot, but small portion of the beef which was a bit disappointing. My company enjoyed the Beef Pho but when I tasted it it seemed like it was missing a bit of flavor.

Recommendation
Definitely recommend for the service and flavor. One of the better Vietnamese restaurants in the area. Maybe there is more to it but also it's a bit strange to have the name and decore more Japanese than Vietnamese. Not taken from the score or rating, just an observation.
Great food and great service, at a very fair price. Had the Vit Exotika

Great Vietnamese. The menu is a little bit light, due to covid-19, but still offers various options. The staff was very friendly and quite quick. The ambiete was very elegant and nicely decorated. The food was great, especially the peanut sauce was really excellent. The prices were expensive, even compared to the other restaurants in the same location. Overall a good experience. I would recommend a visit, if you value Vietnamese dishes.
The food had a good quality, and the portion was very good. I think it is one of the best ducks I have in the city. The service is a little slow tho
Easily one of the best vegetarian Pho in the Stuttgart area. Came here many times already and would recommend.

The food was very tasty, but the crispy chicken was absolutely drenched in oil (way more than what is acceptable).

The service was fast and the people were very nice.

I went for take away, and had the chance to observe how the meals are prepared, as there were multiple orders being handled. The food handling hygienic procedures range from questionable to non existent. No gloves when switching from handling money and change to hand picking ingredients from the containers. Sneezing and coughing either on top of the ingredient and stove, to using the hand to catch a sneeze. The same hand that also picks up the ingredients with no gloves on.

I payed as soon as I ordered, before seeying all of this spectacle, otherwise I would have left. I should have left anyways...
Very delicious and super friendly!!
Amazing place !! Great for takeout

Worst Pad Thai I've ever had.
Flat rice noodles smelled like burnt plastic and everything was very dry. NEVER AGAIN!

editorial_summary.overview: Pan-Asian dishes, cocktails & wines are served in this unpretentious restaurant with a terrace.

reviews.text: Tasty 😋

There are absolutely many things different about this sushi bar. I love the ingredients they used like caviar , lime slices and sprouts. And lotus!!!! It was a long time I didn’t eat lotus and suddenly i ate it here. The salmon sashimi set really worths it. And creamy sushi was very delightful. I really wish i could come here more often if the prices could be more flexible. They work only a few hours a day but they serve very energetic and strongly positive. The take away time is also very reasonable. I am really gonna miss this place when i get far from it one day. Also i love the silver splash of color on the main food stone dish. I don’t know how you found this material but it was so beautiful on the black dish.
Delicious food at a affordable price. Staff speak English and German. They are very polite and warm. I tried the Pho and it was very good. Unfortunately, only cash is accepted for payment.

Great food, authentic taste. Prices are very modest.

We had summer rolls for starters and the rice noodle bowl with beef and fried chicken with wok veggies and a peanuts sauce.

The summer rolls were on point, just like we remember them from our holidays.

The bowl was a delightful mix between wok veggies with beef, cold rice noodles and fresh greens. All very beautifully prepared, though the beef was a bit on the chewy side.

The chicken was tender and we'll done, unfortunately the batter was super coconutty and overshadowed most other flavors. Tasty nonetheless.
Whats better than the foods is the nice-kind people working there

Fantastically sublime flavors and friendly ambience. Service was great and restaurant is comfortable with an old world feel. I just returned from Hanoi and was keen to eat more Vietnamese food. I was very pleased with the menu and authentic flavors offered here. I had the Phở Xào Hải Sản (Fried Rice Noodles With Prawns). This was listed in the menu as spicy. Indeed it was, but it was beautifully balanced with fish sauce and herbs to give the sweet, salt, spice, sour, and lots of umami. Delicious! Paired with a glass of dry white wine and also sampled a special lime juice cocktail which was delicious. Will definitely be back for dine in and takeout.

Amazing place with Amazing Food! This is my wife's and I new favorite place for Tom Ka Gai.. serious good food and the service is Great.. we are a 5min walk from here so we will definitely be coming back again and again.. Thanks y'all.
Amazing food, lovely staff. Been there several times. My place to go. They offer many of the meals in a vegetarian or vegan variant, just ask.

We love this place . We have been there almost everyday for more than a week. Tuan is always so nice to us and very hospitable. The food is great . I have tried several dishes here. My favorite is bun cha ( they have vegan version also ) and the Tom yum soup.
Good food leaves you wanting more and makes you plan to come back again
